{"type":"text","timestamp":1781763191673,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"id":"prt_ed95c9e470015UTv6FsQwTmffg","messageID":"msg_ed95c8b620012uQ3jDF2EWt3q3","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","type":"text","text":"Coverage confirms the environment reference promises `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` accepts `tcp://host:port`, while the shared server resolver has no matching TCP branch. That is a confirmed P1 candidate.","time":{"start":1781763186247,"end":1781763191667},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_081f2e3f85cd21d9016a338c7237088191a2a661e2c923372e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763191757,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jSMaEpzF3JR9By8nkfGYqihv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","offset":172,"limit":16},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n172: | `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG` | `true` | boolean | Persistent launcher log toggle. The mk-spec-memory launcher's `log()` appends a timestamped, pid-stamped line to a durable file in addition to stderr, so daemon flaps and owner-disposal races are attributable from disk even when the host drops stderr. Best-effort (a logging failure never affects the launcher). Set `0` to disable. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n173: | `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_PATH` | `<dbDir>/.mk-spec-memory-launcher.log` | string | Override the persistent launcher log path. The default lives next to the lease in the runtime DB dir and is gitignored via `*.log`. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n174: | `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_MAX_BYTES` | `1048576` | number | Size cap for the persistent launcher log. Once exceeded, the file rotates to a single previous generation (`.prev.log` for a `.log` path, else `<path>.prev`) before the next append, so it cannot grow without bound. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n175: | `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES` | `1` | number | Consecutive deep liveness-probe RETRIES before a sibling launcher reaps the lease owner and respawns. `0` restores single-probe behavior. Requiring N consecutive failures stops a busy-but-alive owner (e.g. mid-FTS-merge) being false-reaped into a duplicate daemon; any 'alive' probe short-circuits to a bridge. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n176: | `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_TIMEOUT_MS` | `1500` | number | Per-attempt timeout (clamped to the 6999ms probe ceiling) for each lease retry probe after the first. Kept short so the default budget (first full probe + one retry + backoff) stays under the launcher grace window. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n177: | `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS` | `250` | number | Backoff between consecutive lease liveness-probe attempts. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n178: | `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP` | `off` | enum | Stop-hook fallback when no `CLAUDE_SESSION_PID` is available. `off` (default) keeps the historical no-op; `dry-run` logs candidate reaps without mutating; `1`/`on`/`live` reaps. Delegates ONLY to the orphan-only `orphan-mcp-sweeper.sh` (ownerless/reparented MCP processes), never a PPID guess, so it cannot kill a live session. | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` |\n179: | `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` | `on` (launcher code default) | boolean | The mk-spec-memory owner spawns the daemon detached and, on shutdown, RELEASES it (keeps the daemon lease, drops only the owner lease) for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so the shared backend outlives its owning session and concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. On by default in the launcher code; set `0` (or `off`) to restore the kill-on-disposal behavior. The release-vs-kill decision is covered by an integration test, and the full two-session behavior is covered by a live durability test that runs two real launchers in isolation; a fresh session after disposal adopts the released daemon through the bridge when the recorded child is alive and bridgeable, and only reaps + respawns when that daemon is dead or unbridgeable, so the database keeps a single writer and the worst case matches the prior behavior. The runtime configs no longer set it; the launcher code is the single source of the default. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n180: | `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` | database directory | string | Overrides the daemon IPC socket directory. **Required on macOS** for production runtimes: the default `<service-db>/daemon-ipc.sock` path exceeds the 104-char `sun_path` limit and `listen()` fails with `EINVAL`. Runtime configs (`.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`) pin each service to a short `/tmp/<service>` directory. Also accepts `tcp://host:port`. Uses `daemon-ipc.sock` as the socket file name. The hf-model-server demand path additionally **fail-fasts** (031/005) with `ESUNPATHTOOLONG` if the resolved socket path exceeds 104 bytes, and refuses a symlinked or foreign-uid-owned socket directory (`ESOCKETDIRSYMLINK`/`ESOCKETDIRFOREIGN`/`ESOCKETSYMLINK`) before binding or reclaiming — perimeter hardening so a hostile/misconfigured dir cannot redirect the socket. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs`, `mcp_server/lib/ipc/socket-server.ts` |\n181: | `SPECKIT_EVAL_DB_PATH` | (null) | string | Custom file path for the eval reporting SQLite database. | `handlers/eval-reporting.ts` |\n182: | `SPECKIT_FORCE_REBIND` | `false` | boolean | Recovery override. When the post-swap rebind guard refuses to rebind consumers to a database reporting 0 memories (suspected path drift), set `true` to force the rebind anyway. Leave unset in normal operation. | `core/db-state.ts` |\n183: | `SPECKIT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWLIST` | (bundled `scripts/lib/frontmatter-grandfather-allowlist.json`) | string | Override path to the spec-doc frontmatter grandfather allowlist JSON used by structural validation. | `lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts` |\n184: | `SPECKIT_VERBOSE_RESOLVER` | `false` | flag (`\"1\"`) | Set `1` to log the underlying cause when the documentation-level contract resolver falls back. Diagnostic only. | `lib/templates/level-contract-resolver.ts` |\n185: | `SPECKIT_STRICT_SCHEMAS` | `true` | boolean | Enforce strict JSON schema validation on MCP tool inputs. Set `false` to relax. | `schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts` |\n186: | `SPECKIT_SKIP_API_VALIDATION` | `false` | boolean | Skip API-level input validation. Opt-in: set `true` to enable. | `context-server.ts` |\n187: | `SPECKIT_BOOT_FTS_AUTOHEAL` | `true` | boolean | Boot-time FTS5 shadow-index auto-heal after an unclean shutdown marker. When unset, the server rebuilds and re-verifies the derived FTS shadow index before serving; set `0` for detect-only mode that logs the failure without attempting the rebuild. | `context-server.ts` |\n\n(Showing lines 172-187 of 652. Use offset=188 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG` | `true` | boolean | Persistent launcher log toggle. The mk-spec-memory launcher's `log()` appends a timestamped, pid-stamped line to a durable file in addition to stderr, so daemon flaps and owner-disposal races are attributable from disk even when the host drops stderr. Best-effort (a logging failure never affects the launcher). Set `0` to disable. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_PATH` | `<dbDir>/.mk-spec-memory-launcher.log` | string | Override the persistent launcher log path. The default lives next to the lease in the runtime DB dir and is gitignored via `*.log`. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_MAX_BYTES` | `1048576` | number | Size cap for the persistent launcher log. Once exceeded, the file rotates to a single previous generation (`.prev.log` for a `.log` path, else `<path>.prev`) before the next append, so it cannot grow without bound. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES` | `1` | number | Consecutive deep liveness-probe RETRIES before a sibling launcher reaps the lease owner and respawns. `0` restores single-probe behavior. Requiring N consecutive failures stops a busy-but-alive owner (e.g. mid-FTS-merge) being false-reaped into a duplicate daemon; any 'alive' probe short-circuits to a bridge. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_TIMEOUT_MS` | `1500` | number | Per-attempt timeout (clamped to the 6999ms probe ceiling) for each lease retry probe after the first. Kept short so the default budget (first full probe + one retry + backoff) stays under the launcher grace window. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS` | `250` | number | Backoff between consecutive lease liveness-probe attempts. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP` | `off` | enum | Stop-hook fallback when no `CLAUDE_SESSION_PID` is available. `off` (default) keeps the historical no-op; `dry-run` logs candidate reaps without mutating; `1`/`on`/`live` reaps. Delegates ONLY to the orphan-only `orphan-mcp-sweeper.sh` (ownerless/reparented MCP processes), never a PPID guess, so it cannot kill a live session. | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` |\n| `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` | `on` (launcher code default) | boolean | The mk-spec-memory owner spawns the daemon detached and, on shutdown, RELEASES it (keeps the daemon lease, drops only the owner lease) for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so the shared backend outlives its owning session and concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. On by default in the launcher code; set `0` (or `off`) to restore the kill-on-disposal behavior. The release-vs-kill decision is covered by an integration test, and the full two-session behavior is covered by a live durability test that runs two real launchers in isolation; a fresh session after disposal adopts the released daemon through the bridge when the recorded child is alive and bridgeable, and only reaps + respawns when that daemon is dead or unbridgeable, so the database keeps a single writer and the worst case matches the prior behavior. The runtime configs no longer set it; the launcher code is the single source of the default. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` | database directory | string | Overrides the daemon IPC socket directory. **Required on macOS** for production runtimes: the default `<service-db>/daemon-ipc.sock` path exceeds the 104-char `sun_path` limit and `listen()` fails with `EINVAL`. Runtime configs (`.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`) pin each service to a short `/tmp/<service>` directory. Also accepts `tcp://host:port`. Uses `daemon-ipc.sock` as the socket file name. The hf-model-server demand path additionally **fail-fasts** (031/005) with `ESUNPATHTOOLONG` if the resolved socket path exceeds 104 bytes, and refuses a symlinked or foreign-uid-owned socket directory (`ESOCKETDIRSYMLINK`/`ESOCKETDIRFOREIGN`/`ESOCKETSYMLINK`) before binding or reclaiming — perimeter hardening so a hostile/misconfigured dir cannot redirect the socket. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs`, `mcp_server/lib/ipc/socket-server.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_EVAL_DB_PATH` | (null) | string | Custom file path for the eval reporting SQLite database. | `handlers/eval-reporting.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FORCE_REBIND` | `false` | boolean | Recovery override. When the post-swap rebind guard refuses to rebind consumers to a database reporting 0 memories (suspected path drift), set `true` to force the rebind anyway. Leave unset in normal operation. | `core/db-state.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWLIST` | (bundled `scripts/lib/frontmatter-grandfather-allowlist.json`) | string | Override path to the spec-doc frontmatter grandfather allowlist JSON used by structural validation. | `lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_VERBOSE_RESOLVER` | `false` | flag (`\"1\"`) | Set `1` to log the underlying cause when the documentation-level contract resolver falls back. Diagnostic only. | `lib/templates/level-contract-resolver.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_STRICT_SCHEMAS` | `true` | boolean | Enforce strict JSON schema validation on MCP tool inputs. Set `false` to relax. | `schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_SKIP_API_VALIDATION` | `false` | boolean | Skip API-level input validation. Opt-in: set `true` to enable. | `context-server.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_BOOT_FTS_AUTOHEAL` | `true` | boolean | Boot-time FTS5 shadow-index auto-heal after an unclean shutdown marker. When unset, the server rebuilds and re-verifies the derived FTS shadow index before serving; set `0` for detect-only mode that logs the failure without attempting the rebuild. | `context-server.ts` |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","text":"| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG` | `true` | boolean | Persistent launcher log toggle. The mk-spec-memory launcher's `log()` appends a timestamped, pid-stamped line to a durable file in addition to stderr, so daemon flaps and owner-disposal races are attributable from disk even when the host drops stderr. Best-effort (a logging failure never affects the launcher). Set `0` to disable. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_PATH` | `<dbDir>/.mk-spec-memory-launcher.log` | string | Override the persistent launcher log path. The default lives next to the lease in the runtime DB dir and is gitignored via `*.log`. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_MAX_BYTES` | `1048576` | number | Size cap for the persistent launcher log. Once exceeded, the file rotates to a single previous generation (`.prev.log` for a `.log` path, else `<path>.prev`) before the next append, so it cannot grow without bound. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES` | `1` | number | Consecutive deep liveness-probe RETRIES before a sibling launcher reaps the lease owner and respawns. `0` restores single-probe behavior. Requiring N consecutive failures stops a busy-but-alive owner (e.g. mid-FTS-merge) being false-reaped into a duplicate daemon; any 'alive' probe short-circuits to a bridge. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_TIMEOUT_MS` | `1500` | number | Per-attempt timeout (clamped to the 6999ms probe ceiling) for each lease retry probe after the first. Kept short so the default budget (first full probe + one retry + backoff) stays under the launcher grace window. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS` | `250` | number | Backoff between consecutive lease liveness-probe attempts. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP` | `off` | enum | Stop-hook fallback when no `CLAUDE_SESSION_PID` is available. `off` (default) keeps the historical no-op; `dry-run` logs candidate reaps without mutating; `1`/`on`/`live` reaps. Delegates ONLY to the orphan-only `orphan-mcp-sweeper.sh` (ownerless/reparented MCP processes), never a PPID guess, so it cannot kill a live session. | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` |\n| `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` | `on` (launcher code default) | boolean | The mk-spec-memory owner spawns the daemon detached and, on shutdown, RELEASES it (keeps the daemon lease, drops only the owner lease) for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so the shared backend outlives its owning session and concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. On by default in the launcher code; set `0` (or `off`) to restore the kill-on-disposal behavior. The release-vs-kill decision is covered by an integration test, and the full two-session behavior is covered by a live durability test that runs two real launchers in isolation; a fresh session after disposal adopts the released daemon through the bridge when the recorded child is alive and bridgeable, and only reaps + respawns when that daemon is dead or unbridgeable, so the database keeps a single writer and the worst case matches the prior behavior. The runtime configs no longer set it; the launcher code is the single source of the default. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` | database directory | string | Overrides the daemon IPC socket directory. **Required on macOS** for production runtimes: the default `<service-db>/daemon-ipc.sock` path exceeds the 104-char `sun_path` limit and `listen()` fails with `EINVAL`. Runtime configs (`.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`) pin each service to a short `/tmp/<service>` directory. Also accepts `tcp://host:port`. Uses `daemon-ipc.sock` as the socket file name. The hf-model-server demand path additionally **fail-fasts** (031/005) with `ESUNPATHTOOLONG` if the resolved socket path exceeds 104 bytes, and refuses a symlinked or foreign-uid-owned socket directory (`ESOCKETDIRSYMLINK`/`ESOCKETDIRFOREIGN`/`ESOCKETSYMLINK`) before binding or reclaiming — perimeter hardening so a hostile/misconfigured dir cannot redirect the socket. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs`, `mcp_server/lib/ipc/socket-server.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_EVAL_DB_PATH` | (null) | string | Custom file path for the eval reporting SQLite database. | `handlers/eval-reporting.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FORCE_REBIND` | `false` | boolean | Recovery override. When the post-swap rebind guard refuses to rebind consumers to a database reporting 0 memories (suspected path drift), set `true` to force the rebind anyway. Leave unset in normal operation. | `core/db-state.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWLIST` | (bundled `scripts/lib/frontmatter-grandfather-allowlist.json`) | string | Override path to the spec-doc frontmatter grandfather allowlist JSON used by structural validation. | `lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_VERBOSE_RESOLVER` | `false` | flag (`\"1\"`) | Set `1` to log the underlying cause when the documentation-level contract resolver falls back. Diagnostic only. | `lib/templates/level-contract-resolver.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_STRICT_SCHEMAS` | `true` | boolean | Enforce strict JSON schema validation on MCP tool inputs. Set `false` to relax. | `schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_SKIP_API_VALIDATION` | `false` | boolean | Skip API-level input validation. Opt-in: set `true` to enable. | `context-server.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_BOOT_FTS_AUTOHEAL` | `true` | boolean | Boot-time FTS5 shadow-index auto-heal after an unclean shutdown marker. When unset, the server rebuilds and re-verifies the derived FTS shadow index before serving; set `0` for detect-only mode that logs the failure without attempting the rebuild. | `context-server.ts` |","lineStart":172,"lineEnd":187,"totalLines":652,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","time":{"start":1781763191747,"end":1781763191755}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_081f2e3f85cd21d9016a338c77927c81918e933cb516819d60"}},"id":"prt_ed95cb3770013IW7v6diWsI5Yp","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95c8b620012uQ3jDF2EWt3q3"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763191785,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ksjcAoakinX7B1Y1vUehMvh7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-ipc-bridge.vitest.ts","offset":300,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-ipc-bridge.vitest.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n300:   });\n301: \n302:   it('refuses clients beyond SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', async () => {\n303:     const sock = 'tcp://127.0.0.1:0';\n304:     let handle: IpcSocketServerHandle;\n305:     try {\n306:       handle = await startIpcSocketServer({ socketPath: sock, createServer: makeServer, maxClients: 8 });\n307:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n308:       if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'EPERM') return;\n309:       throw error;\n310:     }\n311:     handles.push(handle);\n312:     const sockets = await Promise.all(Array.from({ length: 8 }, () => connectSocket(sock)));\n313:     await waitFor(() => getIpcBridgeStats().secondary_clients_count === 8, 'eight active clients');\n314: \n315:     const ninth = await connectSocket(sock);\n316:     await new Promise<void>((resolvePromise) => ninth.once('close', () => resolvePromise()));\n317:     expect(getIpcBridgeStats().secondary_clients_count).toBe(8);\n318:     sockets.forEach((socket) => socket.destroy());\n319:   });\n320: \n321:   it('cleans up the socket file when the listener closes', async () => {\n322:     const dbDir = tempDir('daemon-bridge-cleanup-');\n323:     const unixSock = resolveIpcSocketPath(dbDir);\n324:     expect(unixSock).toBe(join(dbDir, 'daemon-ipc.sock'));\n325:     const sock = 'tcp://127.0.0.1:0';\n326:     let handle: IpcSocketServerHandle;\n327:     try {\n328:       handle = await startIpcSocketServer({ socketPath: sock, createServer: makeServer });\n329:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n330:       if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'EPERM') return;\n331:       throw error;\n332:     }\n333:     expect(getIpcBridgeStats().socket_path).toMatch(/^tcp:\\/\\/127\\.0\\.0\\.1:\\d+$/);\n334:     await handle.close();\n335:     expect(getIpcBridgeStats().socket_path).toBeNull();\n336:   });\n337: });\n\n(End of file - total 337 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  });\n\n  it('refuses clients beyond SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', async () => {\n    const sock = 'tcp://127.0.0.1:0';\n    let handle: IpcSocketServerHandle;\n    try {\n      handle = await startIpcSocketServer({ socketPath: sock, createServer: makeServer, maxClients: 8 });\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'EPERM') return;\n      throw error;\n    }\n    handles.push(handle);\n    const sockets = await Promise.all(Array.from({ length: 8 }, () => connectSocket(sock)));\n    await waitFor(() => getIpcBridgeStats().secondary_clients_count === 8, 'eight active clients');\n\n    const ninth = await connectSocket(sock);\n    await new Promise<void>((resolvePromise) => ninth.once('close', () => resolvePromise()));\n    expect(getIpcBridgeStats().secondary_clients_count).toBe(8);\n    sockets.forEach((socket) => socket.destroy());\n  });","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-ipc-bridge.vitest.ts","text":"  });\n\n  it('refuses clients beyond SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', async () => {\n    const sock = 'tcp://127.0.0.1:0';\n    let handle: IpcSocketServerHandle;\n    try {\n      handle = await startIpcSocketServer({ socketPath: sock, createServer: makeServer, maxClients: 8 });\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'EPERM') return;\n      throw error;\n    }\n    handles.push(handle);\n    const sockets = await Promise.all(Array.from({ length: 8 }, () => connectSocket(sock)));\n    await waitFor(() => getIpcBridgeStats().secondary_clients_count === 8, 'eight active clients');\n\n    const ninth = await connectSocket(sock);\n    await new Promise<void>((resolvePromise) => ninth.once('close', () => resolvePromise()));\n    expect(getIpcBridgeStats().secondary_clients_count).toBe(8);\n    sockets.forEach((socket) => socket.destroy());\n  });\n\n  it('cleans up the socket file when the listener closes', async () => {\n    const dbDir = tempDir('daemon-bridge-cleanup-');\n    const unixSock = resolveIpcSocketPath(dbDir);\n    expect(unixSock).toBe(join(dbDir, 'daemon-ipc.sock'));\n    const sock = 'tcp://127.0.0.1:0';\n    let handle: IpcSocketServerHandle;\n    try {\n      handle = await startIpcSocketServer({ socketPath: sock, createServer: makeServer });\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'EPERM') return;\n      throw error;\n    }\n    expect(getIpcBridgeStats().socket_path).toMatch(/^tcp:\\/\\/127\\.0\\.0\\.1:\\d+$/);\n    await handle.close();\n    expect(getIpcBridgeStats().socket_path).toBeNull();\n  });\n});","lineStart":300,"lineEnd":337,"totalLines":337,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-ipc-bridge.vitest.ts","time":{"start":1781763191775,"end":1781763191781}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_081f2e3f85cd21d9016a338c7792a08191a6ad10996e82c3d5"}},"id":"prt_ed95cb3d7001L3mNUwRurUF3PZ","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95c8b620012uQ3jDF2EWt3q3"}}
