{"type":"text","timestamp":1781763337322,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"id":"prt_ed95ed10e001yuMLxvXtQt0hIj","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","type":"text","text":"Evidence is sufficient to proceed: two P1 data-integrity/availability findings, no confirmed P0 because each requires a specific operator setting or mid-recycle timing rather than deterministic corruption on every run.","time":{"start":1781763330318,"end":1781763337321},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0985248d89c97d30016a338d02495c81918fe9807d365421ce","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763337379,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OYXPetNVeNZDZKuChQmQt0ZM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-c-6","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-c-6</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.executor-state/\n\n(1 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".executor-state/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-c-6","entries":[".executor-state/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-c-6","time":{"start":1781763337363,"end":1781763337369}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0985248d89c97d30016a338d0942608191b25d81d8094d6fce"}},"id":"prt_ed95eec6d001P1titAoL94rGa1","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763337400,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_N5DaFlzhHkBLPT9rAaRd4KNv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs","offset":104,"limit":14},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n104:   if (!process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR) {\n105:     process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = defaultSocketDir;\n106:   }\n107:   const socketDir = process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR;\n108:   if (socketDir.startsWith('tcp://')) return;\n109:   fs.mkdirSync(socketDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n110:   const socketPath = path.join(path.resolve(socketDir), socketFileName);\n111:   if (process.platform === 'darwin' && Buffer.byteLength(socketPath) > 103) {\n112:     fail(`spec-memory socket path exceeds the Darwin sun_path limit: ${socketPath}. Set SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR to a shorter directory or a tcp:// endpoint.`);\n113:   }\n114: }\n115: \n116: ensureSocketDir();\n117: ensureFreshDist();\n\n(Showing lines 104-117 of 130. Use offset=118 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  if (!process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR) {\n    process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = defaultSocketDir;\n  }\n  const socketDir = process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR;\n  if (socketDir.startsWith('tcp://')) return;\n  fs.mkdirSync(socketDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n  const socketPath = path.join(path.resolve(socketDir), socketFileName);\n  if (process.platform === 'darwin' && Buffer.byteLength(socketPath) > 103) {\n    fail(`spec-memory socket path exceeds the Darwin sun_path limit: ${socketPath}. Set SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR to a shorter directory or a tcp:// endpoint.`);\n  }\n}\n\nensureSocketDir();\nensureFreshDist();","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs","text":"  if (!process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR) {\n    process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = defaultSocketDir;\n  }\n  const socketDir = process.env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR;\n  if (socketDir.startsWith('tcp://')) return;\n  fs.mkdirSync(socketDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n  const socketPath = path.join(path.resolve(socketDir), socketFileName);\n  if (process.platform === 'darwin' && Buffer.byteLength(socketPath) > 103) {\n    fail(`spec-memory socket path exceeds the Darwin sun_path limit: ${socketPath}. Set SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR to a shorter directory or a tcp:// endpoint.`);\n  }\n}\n\nensureSocketDir();\nensureFreshDist();","lineStart":104,"lineEnd":117,"totalLines":130,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs","time":{"start":1781763337389,"end":1781763337395}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0985248d89c97d30016a338d09428c81918d48bdf71d9601ca"}},"id":"prt_ed95eecaa001QRR9UJ20O23m6b","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763337400,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MvXkAv5syiESh4kWHZFTOyk2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","offset":174,"limit":10},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n174: | `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_MAX_BYTES` | `1048576` | number | Size cap for the persistent launcher log. Once exceeded, the file rotates to a single previous generation (`.prev.log` for a `.log` path, else `<path>.prev`) before the next append, so it cannot grow without bound. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n175: | `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES` | `1` | number | Consecutive deep liveness-probe RETRIES before a sibling launcher reaps the lease owner and respawns. `0` restores single-probe behavior. Requiring N consecutive failures stops a busy-but-alive owner (e.g. mid-FTS-merge) being false-reaped into a duplicate daemon; any 'alive' probe short-circuits to a bridge. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n176: | `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_TIMEOUT_MS` | `1500` | number | Per-attempt timeout (clamped to the 6999ms probe ceiling) for each lease retry probe after the first. Kept short so the default budget (first full probe + one retry + backoff) stays under the launcher grace window. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n177: | `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS` | `250` | number | Backoff between consecutive lease liveness-probe attempts. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n178: | `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP` | `off` | enum | Stop-hook fallback when no `CLAUDE_SESSION_PID` is available. `off` (default) keeps the historical no-op; `dry-run` logs candidate reaps without mutating; `1`/`on`/`live` reaps. Delegates ONLY to the orphan-only `orphan-mcp-sweeper.sh` (ownerless/reparented MCP processes), never a PPID guess, so it cannot kill a live session. | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` |\n179: | `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` | `on` (launcher code default) | boolean | The mk-spec-memory owner spawns the daemon detached and, on shutdown, RELEASES it (keeps the daemon lease, drops only the owner lease) for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so the shared backend outlives its owning session and concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. On by default in the launcher code; set `0` (or `off`) to restore the kill-on-disposal behavior. The release-vs-kill decision is covered by an integration test, and the full two-session behavior is covered by a live durability test that runs two real launchers in isolation; a fresh session after disposal adopts the released daemon through the bridge when the recorded child is alive and bridgeable, and only reaps + respawns when that daemon is dead or unbridgeable, so the database keeps a single writer and the worst case matches the prior behavior. The runtime configs no longer set it; the launcher code is the single source of the default. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n180: | `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` | database directory | string | Overrides the daemon IPC socket directory. **Required on macOS** for production runtimes: the default `<service-db>/daemon-ipc.sock` path exceeds the 104-char `sun_path` limit and `listen()` fails with `EINVAL`. Runtime configs (`.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`) pin each service to a short `/tmp/<service>` directory. Also accepts `tcp://host:port`. Uses `daemon-ipc.sock` as the socket file name. The hf-model-server demand path additionally **fail-fasts** (031/005) with `ESUNPATHTOOLONG` if the resolved socket path exceeds 104 bytes, and refuses a symlinked or foreign-uid-owned socket directory (`ESOCKETDIRSYMLINK`/`ESOCKETDIRFOREIGN`/`ESOCKETSYMLINK`) before binding or reclaiming — perimeter hardening so a hostile/misconfigured dir cannot redirect the socket. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs`, `mcp_server/lib/ipc/socket-server.ts` |\n181: | `SPECKIT_EVAL_DB_PATH` | (null) | string | Custom file path for the eval reporting SQLite database. | `handlers/eval-reporting.ts` |\n182: | `SPECKIT_FORCE_REBIND` | `false` | boolean | Recovery override. When the post-swap rebind guard refuses to rebind consumers to a database reporting 0 memories (suspected path drift), set `true` to force the rebind anyway. Leave unset in normal operation. | `core/db-state.ts` |\n183: | `SPECKIT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWLIST` | (bundled `scripts/lib/frontmatter-grandfather-allowlist.json`) | string | Override path to the spec-doc frontmatter grandfather allowlist JSON used by structural validation. | `lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts` |\n\n(Showing lines 174-183 of 652. Use offset=184 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_MAX_BYTES` | `1048576` | number | Size cap for the persistent launcher log. Once exceeded, the file rotates to a single previous generation (`.prev.log` for a `.log` path, else `<path>.prev`) before the next append, so it cannot grow without bound. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES` | `1` | number | Consecutive deep liveness-probe RETRIES before a sibling launcher reaps the lease owner and respawns. `0` restores single-probe behavior. Requiring N consecutive failures stops a busy-but-alive owner (e.g. mid-FTS-merge) being false-reaped into a duplicate daemon; any 'alive' probe short-circuits to a bridge. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_TIMEOUT_MS` | `1500` | number | Per-attempt timeout (clamped to the 6999ms probe ceiling) for each lease retry probe after the first. Kept short so the default budget (first full probe + one retry + backoff) stays under the launcher grace window. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS` | `250` | number | Backoff between consecutive lease liveness-probe attempts. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP` | `off` | enum | Stop-hook fallback when no `CLAUDE_SESSION_PID` is available. `off` (default) keeps the historical no-op; `dry-run` logs candidate reaps without mutating; `1`/`on`/`live` reaps. Delegates ONLY to the orphan-only `orphan-mcp-sweeper.sh` (ownerless/reparented MCP processes), never a PPID guess, so it cannot kill a live session. | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` |\n| `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` | `on` (launcher code default) | boolean | The mk-spec-memory owner spawns the daemon detached and, on shutdown, RELEASES it (keeps the daemon lease, drops only the owner lease) for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so the shared backend outlives its owning session and concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. On by default in the launcher code; set `0` (or `off`) to restore the kill-on-disposal behavior. The release-vs-kill decision is covered by an integration test, and the full two-session behavior is covered by a live durability test that runs two real launchers in isolation; a fresh session after disposal adopts the released daemon through the bridge when the recorded child is alive and bridgeable, and only reaps + respawns when that daemon is dead or unbridgeable, so the database keeps a single writer and the worst case matches the prior behavior. The runtime configs no longer set it; the launcher code is the single source of the default. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` | database directory | string | Overrides the daemon IPC socket directory. **Required on macOS** for production runtimes: the default `<service-db>/daemon-ipc.sock` path exceeds the 104-char `sun_path` limit and `listen()` fails with `EINVAL`. Runtime configs (`.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`) pin each service to a short `/tmp/<service>` directory. Also accepts `tcp://host:port`. Uses `daemon-ipc.sock` as the socket file name. The hf-model-server demand path additionally **fail-fasts** (031/005) with `ESUNPATHTOOLONG` if the resolved socket path exceeds 104 bytes, and refuses a symlinked or foreign-uid-owned socket directory (`ESOCKETDIRSYMLINK`/`ESOCKETDIRFOREIGN`/`ESOCKETSYMLINK`) before binding or reclaiming — perimeter hardening so a hostile/misconfigured dir cannot redirect the socket. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs`, `mcp_server/lib/ipc/socket-server.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_EVAL_DB_PATH` | (null) | string | Custom file path for the eval reporting SQLite database. | `handlers/eval-reporting.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FORCE_REBIND` | `false` | boolean | Recovery override. When the post-swap rebind guard refuses to rebind consumers to a database reporting 0 memories (suspected path drift), set `true` to force the rebind anyway. Leave unset in normal operation. | `core/db-state.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWLIST` | (bundled `scripts/lib/frontmatter-grandfather-allowlist.json`) | string | Override path to the spec-doc frontmatter grandfather allowlist JSON used by structural validation. | `lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts` |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","text":"| `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG_MAX_BYTES` | `1048576` | number | Size cap for the persistent launcher log. Once exceeded, the file rotates to a single previous generation (`.prev.log` for a `.log` path, else `<path>.prev`) before the next append, so it cannot grow without bound. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES` | `1` | number | Consecutive deep liveness-probe RETRIES before a sibling launcher reaps the lease owner and respawns. `0` restores single-probe behavior. Requiring N consecutive failures stops a busy-but-alive owner (e.g. mid-FTS-merge) being false-reaped into a duplicate daemon; any 'alive' probe short-circuits to a bridge. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_TIMEOUT_MS` | `1500` | number | Per-attempt timeout (clamped to the 6999ms probe ceiling) for each lease retry probe after the first. Kept short so the default budget (first full probe + one retry + backoff) stays under the launcher grace window. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS` | `250` | number | Backoff between consecutive lease liveness-probe attempts. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP` | `off` | enum | Stop-hook fallback when no `CLAUDE_SESSION_PID` is available. `off` (default) keeps the historical no-op; `dry-run` logs candidate reaps without mutating; `1`/`on`/`live` reaps. Delegates ONLY to the orphan-only `orphan-mcp-sweeper.sh` (ownerless/reparented MCP processes), never a PPID guess, so it cannot kill a live session. | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` |\n| `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` | `on` (launcher code default) | boolean | The mk-spec-memory owner spawns the daemon detached and, on shutdown, RELEASES it (keeps the daemon lease, drops only the owner lease) for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so the shared backend outlives its owning session and concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. On by default in the launcher code; set `0` (or `off`) to restore the kill-on-disposal behavior. The release-vs-kill decision is covered by an integration test, and the full two-session behavior is covered by a live durability test that runs two real launchers in isolation; a fresh session after disposal adopts the released daemon through the bridge when the recorded child is alive and bridgeable, and only reaps + respawns when that daemon is dead or unbridgeable, so the database keeps a single writer and the worst case matches the prior behavior. The runtime configs no longer set it; the launcher code is the single source of the default. | `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` |\n| `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR` | database directory | string | Overrides the daemon IPC socket directory. **Required on macOS** for production runtimes: the default `<service-db>/daemon-ipc.sock` path exceeds the 104-char `sun_path` limit and `listen()` fails with `EINVAL`. Runtime configs (`.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`) pin each service to a short `/tmp/<service>` directory. Also accepts `tcp://host:port`. Uses `daemon-ipc.sock` as the socket file name. The hf-model-server demand path additionally **fail-fasts** (031/005) with `ESUNPATHTOOLONG` if the resolved socket path exceeds 104 bytes, and refuses a symlinked or foreign-uid-owned socket directory (`ESOCKETDIRSYMLINK`/`ESOCKETDIRFOREIGN`/`ESOCKETSYMLINK`) before binding or reclaiming — perimeter hardening so a hostile/misconfigured dir cannot redirect the socket. | `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs`, `mcp_server/lib/ipc/socket-server.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_EVAL_DB_PATH` | (null) | string | Custom file path for the eval reporting SQLite database. | `handlers/eval-reporting.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FORCE_REBIND` | `false` | boolean | Recovery override. When the post-swap rebind guard refuses to rebind consumers to a database reporting 0 memories (suspected path drift), set `true` to force the rebind anyway. Leave unset in normal operation. | `core/db-state.ts` |\n| `SPECKIT_FRONTMATTER_ALLOWLIST` | (bundled `scripts/lib/frontmatter-grandfather-allowlist.json`) | string | Override path to the spec-doc frontmatter grandfather allowlist JSON used by structural validation. | `lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts` |","lineStart":174,"lineEnd":183,"totalLines":652,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md","time":{"start":1781763337377,"end":1781763337399}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0985248d89c97d30016a338d09428481918c0485c6b1663086"}},"id":"prt_ed95eec9f001EAIbEoWqOx7GI7","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763337409,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Mjg6RfWXuOOG3NzGWqpnCOmn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_jsonl.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review State Log Records\n3: description: JSONL state-log record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema v2 for the deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"review jsonl record schemas\"\n7:   - \"review depth schema\"\n8:   - \"review traceability checks\"\n9:   - \"review graph events\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Log Records\n15: \n16: The `deep-review-state.jsonl` log is the append-only source of truth for a review run. This reference documents the config, iteration, event, and lineage record schemas plus the Review Depth Schema (v2) that the reducer consumes.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: This reference defines the append-only JSONL records that preserve deep-review run state. It covers config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, verdict, traceability, and Review Depth Schema v2 records so reducers and validators can replay the loop deterministically.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Validating `deep-review-state.jsonl` shape before changing reducers, dashboards, or workflow emission.\n29: - Debugging malformed state records, blocked-stop events, graph convergence events, or lineage fields.\n30: - Adding or checking Review Depth Schema v2 target selection, search coverage, and ledger fields.\n31: - Confirming which fields are required before writing iteration, synthesis, pause, or recovery events.\n32: \n33: ### Key Sources\n34: \n35: | Source | Purpose |\n36: |--------|---------|\n37: | Config record | Establishes session identity, lineage, thresholds, and spec folder routing. |\n38: | Iteration record | Captures focus, reviewed files, findings, convergence ratios, and graph events. |\n39: | Event records | Persist synthesis, blocked-stop, graph convergence, pause, and stuck-recovery decisions. |\n40: | Review Depth Schema v2 | Adds target selection, search coverage, and ledger proof for deeper review iterations. |\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 2. STATE LOG (DEEP-REVIEW-STATE.JSONL)\n45: \n46: Append-only JSON Lines file. One JSON object per line.\n47: \n48: ### Line 1: Config Record\n49: \n50: ```json\n51: {\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"topic\":\"...\",\"reviewTarget\":\"...\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-...\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":7,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.10,\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\"specFolder\":\"...\"}\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Iteration Records\n55: \n56: ```json\n57: {\n58:   \"type\": \"iteration\", \"mode\": \"review\", \"run\": 3, \"status\": \"complete\",\n59:   \"focus\": \"D3 Traceability - skill/runtime alignment\",\n60:   \"dimensions\": [\"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n61:   \"filesReviewed\": [\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/README.md\"],\n62:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n63:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n64:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n65:   \"generation\": 1,\n66:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n67:   \"findingsCount\": 4,\n68:   \"findingsSummary\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 3 },\n69:   \"findingsNew\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 1 },\n70:   \"findingDetails\": [\n71:     {\n72:       \"id\": \"P1-001\",\n73:       \"severity\": \"P1\",\n74:       \"title\": \"Missing consumer update\",\n75:       \"dimension\": \"correctness\",\n76:       \"file\": \"path/to/file.ts:42\",\n77:       \"evidence\": \"Observed consumer still reads the old field.\",\n78:       \"recommendation\": \"Update the consumer and add verification.\",\n79:       \"disposition\": \"active\",\n80:       \"findingClass\": \"cross-consumer\",\n81:       \"scopeProof\": \"rg evidence covering producers and consumers\",\n82:       \"affectedSurfaceHints\": [\"producer/helper\", \"consumer/status\"]\n83:     }\n84:   ],\n85:   \"newFindingsRatio\": 0.32,\n86:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T14:30:00Z\", \"durationMs\": 52000\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: **Required fields:** `type`, `mode`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, `durationMs`\n91: \n92: **Optional fields:** `parentSessionId`, `continuedFromRun`, `findingsRefined`, `findingRefs`, `traceabilityChecks`, `coverage`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `focusTrack`, `scoreEstimate`, `segment`, `convergenceSignals`, `graphEvents`\n93: \n94: | Required Field | Type | Description |\n95: |---------------|------|-------------|\n96: | mode | `\"review\"` | Session mode discriminator |\n97: | dimensions | string[] | Review dimensions addressed this iteration |\n98: | filesReviewed | string[] | Files examined |\n99: | sessionId | string | Current lineage session identifier |\n100: | generation | number | Lineage generation number |\n101: | lineageMode | string | Lifecycle mode used for this run |\n102: | findingsSummary | object | Total active findings: `{ P0, P1, P2 }` |\n103: | findingsNew | object | Net-new findings this iteration: `{ P0, P1, P2 }` |\n104: | findingDetails | array | Active findings with `id`, `severity`, `title`, `dimension`, `file`, `evidence`, `recommendation`, `disposition`, `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints`, use `[]` when there are no findings |\n105: | newFindingsRatio | number | Severity-weighted new findings ratio (0.0-1.0) |\n106: \n107: ### Convergence Signals\n108: \n109: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n110: |--------|--------|-------------|\n111: | rollingAvg | 0.30 | Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings |\n112: | madScore | 0.25 | Noise-floor test against MAD-derived churn |\n113: | dimensionCoverage | 0.45 | Required dimension + protocol coverage stability |\n114: | compositeStop | -- | Weighted stop score (stop if > 0.60) |\n115: \n116: **Severity math:** `refinementMultiplier: 0.5`, `p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50`, `noFindingsRatio: 0.0`\n117: \n118: ### Graph Events\n119: \n120: The optional `graphEvents` array records coverage graph mutations emitted by a review iteration. The MCP coverage graph handlers (`mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`) consume these events and persist them into `deep-loop-graph.sqlite`, where they become the source of truth for graph-assisted convergence, hotspot saturation, and blocked-stop evidence.\n121: \n122: ```json\n123: {\n124:   \"type\": \"iteration\", \"mode\": \"review\", \"run\": 4, \"status\": \"complete\",\n125:   \"focus\": \"correctness\",\n126:   \"dimensions\": [\"correctness\"],\n127:   \"filesReviewed\": [\"src/api/session.ts\"],\n128:   \"findingsSummary\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 0 },\n129:   \"findingsNew\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 0 },\n130:   \"newFindingsRatio\": 0.18,\n131:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n132:   \"generation\": 1,\n133:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n134:   \"graphEvents\": [\n135:     { \"type\": \"dimension\", \"id\": \"d-correctness\", \"label\": \"correctness\" },\n136:     { \"type\": \"file\", \"id\": \"file-session-ts\", \"label\": \"src/api/session.ts\" },\n137:     { \"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-001\", \"label\": \"Missing CSRF token check on session POST\" },\n138:     { \"type\": \"evidence\", \"id\": \"ev-001\", \"label\": \"src/api/session.ts:42\" },\n139:     { \"type\": \"edge\", \"id\": \"e-in-dim-f-001\", \"relation\": \"IN_DIMENSION\", \"source\": \"f-001\", \"target\": \"d-correctness\" },\n140:     { \"type\": \"edge\", \"id\": \"e-in-file-f-001\", \"relation\": \"IN_FILE\", \"source\": \"f-001\", \"target\": \"file-session-ts\" },\n141:     { \"type\": \"edge\", \"id\": \"e-evidence-f-001\", \"relation\": \"EVIDENCE_FOR\", \"source\": \"ev-001\", \"target\": \"f-001\" }\n142:   ],\n143:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T10:12:00Z\",\n144:   \"durationMs\": 51000\n145: }\n146: ```\n147: \n148: #### Event payload shape\n149: \n150: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n151: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n152: | type | `\"dimension\"` \\| `\"file\"` \\| `\"finding\"` \\| `\"evidence\"` \\| `\"remediation\"` \\| `\"edge\"` | Yes | Review-loop node kind or the literal `\"edge\"` for relation rows |\n153: | id | string | Yes | Caller-chosen logical id. Must be unique **within** a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace, see Namespace Rules below |\n154: | label | string | Yes | Human-readable name/caption (dimension, path, finding title, evidence anchor, etc.) |\n155: | relation | `\"COVERS\"` \\| `\"EVIDENCE_FOR\"` \\| `\"CONTRADICTS\"` \\| `\"RESOLVES\"` \\| `\"CONFIRMS\"` \\| `\"ESCALATES\"` \\| `\"IN_DIMENSION\"` \\| `\"IN_FILE\"` | edges only | Review relation type. Required when `type == \"edge\"` |\n156: | source | string | edges only | `id` of the source node inside the current namespace |\n157: | target | string | edges only | `id` of the target node inside the current namespace. Self-loops are rejected by the upsert handler |\n158: | metadata | object | No | Optional free-form metadata persisted alongside the row (e.g. `{ \"hotspot_score\": 2 }`) |\n159: \n160: #### Namespace Rules (REQ-028, REQ-029)\n161: \n162: `graphEvents` entries are scoped by the session that emits them. The coverage graph DB uses a composite primary key of `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)`, so two independent review sessions in the same spec folder MAY reuse the same logical `id` without collision, each session gets its own row.\n163: \n164: Concrete obligations for producers:\n165: \n166: 1. **Session-local uniqueness**: within one session, an `id` must resolve to exactly one node (or edge) for its entire lifetime. Re-emitting the same `id` is an upsert against the existing row in that session only.\n167: 2. **No cross-session global uniqueness requirement**: callers MUST NOT prefix ids with the session id or random salt to \"avoid collisions\". The DB layer handles namespace isolation. Salting ids only makes provenance harder to read.\n168: 3. **Edge source/target locality**: `source` and `target` in an edge event must name nodes already present in the same namespace. Cross-session edges are not a supported shape.\n169: 4. **Persistence gate**: the reducer refuses to roll graph events forward when a record is missing `sessionId` on the surrounding iteration record, because the DB cannot route the write.\n170: \n171: The collision regression in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/session-isolation.vitest.ts` (\"shared-ID collisions\" block) exercises this contract directly: two sessions upsert identical node and edge ids, and both rows must survive independently.\n172: \n173: ### Synthesis Event\n174: \n175: ```json\n176: {\n177:   \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\", \"mode\": \"review\",\n178:   \"totalIterations\": 6, \"verdict\": \"PASS\",\n179:   \"activeP0\": 0, \"activeP1\": 0, \"activeP2\": 2,\n180:   \"dimensionCoverage\": 1.0, \"stopReason\": \"composite_converged\",\n181:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\"\n182: }\n183: ```\n184: \n185: **Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `totalIterations`, `verdict`, `activeP0`, `activeP1`, `activeP2`, `dimensionCoverage`, `stopReason`, `timestamp`\n186: \n187: ### Blocked-Stop Event\n188: \n189: When the review legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, append a first-class `blocked_stop` event instead of silently overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\n190: \n191: ```json\n192: {\n193:   \"type\": \"event\",\n194:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n195:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n196:   \"run\": 4,\n197:   \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n198:   \"gateResults\": {\n199:     \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n200:     \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n201:       \"pass\": false,\n202:       \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\"],\n203:       \"missing\": [\"traceability\", \"maintainability\"]\n204:     },\n205:     \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n206:     \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.5 },\n207:     \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n208:     \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n209:     \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n210:     \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n211:     \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n212:   },\n213:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Cover the missing review dimensions, then resolve the active P0.\",\n214:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T09:45:00Z\",\n215:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-11T09-00-00Z\",\n216:   \"generation\": 1\n217: }\n218: ```\n219: \n220: `gateResults` carries the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. The last two are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. See `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 for the authoritative shape.\n221: \n222: **Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `run`, `blockedBy`, `gateResults`, `recoveryStrategy`, `timestamp`, `sessionId`, `generation`\n223: \n224: ### Graph Convergence Event\n225: \n226: Before the inline 3-signal review vote is allowed to finalize STOP, the workflow must append a `graph_convergence` event for the current review lineage.\n227: \n228: ```json\n229: {\n230:   \"type\": \"event\",\n231:   \"event\": \"graph_convergence\",\n232:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n233:   \"run\": 4,\n234:   \"decision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n235:   \"signals\": {\n236:     \"dimensionCoverage\": 1,\n237:     \"findingStability\": 0.88,\n238:     \"p0ResolutionRate\": 1,\n239:     \"evidenceDensity\": 1.4,\n240:     \"hotspotSaturation\": 0.75\n241:   },\n242:   \"blockers\": [],\n243:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T09:44:00Z\",\n244:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-11T09-00-00Z\",\n245:   \"generation\": 1\n246: }\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `run`, `decision`, `signals`, `blockers`, `timestamp`, `sessionId`, `generation`\n250: \n251: **Decision enum:** `CONTINUE`, `STOP_ALLOWED`, `STOP_BLOCKED`\n252: \n253: **Combined-stop rule:** Final STOP is legal only when the inline review convergence decision says STOP and the latest `graph_convergence.decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\"`. If the latest graph decision is `STOP_BLOCKED`, set `stop_blocked=true`, emit `blocked_stop`, and continue recovery instead of stopping. If the latest graph decision is `CONTINUE`, downgrade the inline STOP candidate to CONTINUE.\n254: \n255: ### Normalized Pause and Recovery Events\n256: \n257: Pause and recovery events MUST use the frozen shared stop-reason enum at emission time:\n258: \n259: `converged`, `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `error`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`\n260: \n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 462. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Log Records\ndescription: JSONL state-log record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema v2 for the deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state jsonl\"\n  - \"review jsonl record schemas\"\n  - \"review depth schema\"\n  - \"review traceability checks\"\n  - \"review graph events\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Log Records\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` log is the append-only source of truth for a review run. This reference documents the config, iteration, event, and lineage record schemas plus the Review Depth Schema (v2) that the reducer consumes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Log Records\ndescription: JSONL state-log record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema v2 for the deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state jsonl\"\n  - \"review jsonl record schemas\"\n  - \"review depth schema\"\n  - \"review traceability checks\"\n  - \"review graph events\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Log Records\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` log is the append-only source of truth for a review run. This reference documents the config, iteration, event, and lineage record schemas plus the Review Depth Schema (v2) that the reducer consumes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThis reference defines the append-only JSONL records that preserve deep-review run state. It covers config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, verdict, traceability, and Review Depth Schema v2 records so reducers and validators can replay the loop deterministically.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Validating `deep-review-state.jsonl` shape before changing reducers, dashboards, or workflow emission.\n- Debugging malformed state records, blocked-stop events, graph convergence events, or lineage fields.\n- Adding or checking Review Depth Schema v2 target selection, search coverage, and ledger fields.\n- Confirming which fields are required before writing iteration, synthesis, pause, or recovery events.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n| Source | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| Config record | Establishes session identity, lineage, thresholds, and spec folder routing. |\n| Iteration record | Captures focus, reviewed files, findings, convergence ratios, and graph events. |\n| Event records | Persist synthesis, blocked-stop, graph convergence, pause, and stuck-recovery decisions. |\n| Review Depth Schema v2 | Adds target selection, search coverage, and ledger proof for deeper review iterations. |\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATE LOG (DEEP-REVIEW-STATE.JSONL)\n\nAppend-only JSON Lines file. One JSON object per line.\n\n### Line 1: Config Record\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"topic\":\"...\",\"reviewTarget\":\"...\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-...\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":7,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.10,\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\"specFolder\":\"...\"}\n```\n\n### Iteration Records\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\", \"mode\": \"review\", \"run\": 3, \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"D3 Traceability - skill/runtime alignment\",\n  \"dimensions\": [\"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n  \"filesReviewed\": [\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/README.md\"],\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"findingsCount\": 4,\n  \"findingsSummary\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 3 },\n  \"findingsNew\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 1 },\n  \"findingDetails\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-001\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"title\": \"Missing consumer update\",\n      \"dimension\": \"correctness\",\n      \"file\": \"path/to/file.ts:42\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Observed consumer still reads the old field.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Update the consumer and add verification.\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"findingClass\": \"cross-consumer\",\n      \"scopeProof\": \"rg evidence covering producers and consumers\",\n      \"affectedSurfaceHints\": [\"producer/helper\", \"consumer/status\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"newFindingsRatio\": 0.32,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T14:30:00Z\", \"durationMs\": 52000\n}\n```\n\n**Required fields:** `type`, `mode`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, `durationMs`\n\n**Optional fields:** `parentSessionId`, `continuedFromRun`, `findingsRefined`, `findingRefs`, `traceabilityChecks`, `coverage`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `focusTrack`, `scoreEstimate`, `segment`, `convergenceSignals`, `graphEvents`\n\n| Required Field | Type | Description |\n|---------------|------|-------------|\n| mode | `\"review\"` | Session mode discriminator |\n| dimensions | string[] | Review dimensions addressed this iteration |\n| filesReviewed | string[] | Files examined |\n| sessionId | string | Current lineage session identifier |\n| generation | number | Lineage generation number |\n| lineageMode | string | Lifecycle mode used for this run |\n| findingsSummary | object | Total active findings: `{ P0, P1, P2 }` |\n| findingsNew | object | Net-new findings this iteration: `{ P0, P1, P2 }` |\n| findingDetails | array | Active findings with `id`, `severity`, `title`, `dimension`, `file`, `evidence`, `recommendation`, `disposition`, `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints`, use `[]` when there are no findings |\n| newFindingsRatio | number | Severity-weighted new findings ratio (0.0-1.0) |\n\n### Convergence Signals\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| rollingAvg | 0.30 | Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings |\n| madScore | 0.25 | Noise-floor test against MAD-derived churn |\n| dimensionCoverage | 0.45 | Required dimension + protocol coverage stability |\n| compositeStop | -- | Weighted stop score (stop if > 0.60) |\n\n**Severity math:** `refinementMultiplier: 0.5`, `p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50`, `noFindingsRatio: 0.0`\n\n### Graph Events\n\nThe optional `graphEvents` array records coverage graph mutations emitted by a review iteration. The MCP coverage graph handlers (`mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`) consume these events and persist them into `deep-loop-graph.sqlite`, where they become the source of truth for graph-assisted convergence, hotspot saturation, and blocked-stop evidence.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\", \"mode\": \"review\", \"run\": 4, \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"correctness\",\n  \"dimensions\": [\"correctness\"],\n  \"filesReviewed\": [\"src/api/session.ts\"],\n  \"findingsSummary\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 0 },\n  \"findingsNew\": { \"P0\": 0, \"P1\": 1, \"P2\": 0 },\n  \"newFindingsRatio\": 0.18,\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    { \"type\": \"dimension\", \"id\": \"d-correctness\", \"label\": \"correctness\" },\n    { \"type\": \"file\", \"id\": \"file-session-ts\", \"label\": \"src/api/session.ts\" },\n    { \"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-001\", \"label\": \"Missing CSRF token check on session POST\" },\n    { \"type\": \"evidence\", \"id\": \"ev-001\", \"label\": \"src/api/session.ts:42\" },\n    { \"type\": \"edge\", \"id\": \"e-in-dim-f-001\", \"relation\": \"IN_DIMENSION\", \"source\": \"f-001\", \"target\": \"d-correctness\" },\n    { \"type\": \"edge\", \"id\": \"e-in-file-f-001\", \"relation\": \"IN_FILE\", \"source\": \"f-001\", \"target\": \"file-session-ts\" },\n    { \"type\": \"edge\", \"id\": \"e-evidence-f-001\", \"relation\": \"EVIDENCE_FOR\", \"source\": \"ev-001\", \"target\": \"f-001\" }\n  ],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T10:12:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 51000\n}\n```\n\n#### Event payload shape\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| type | `\"dimension\"` \\| `\"file\"` \\| `\"finding\"` \\| `\"evidence\"` \\| `\"remediation\"` \\| `\"edge\"` | Yes | Review-loop node kind or the literal `\"edge\"` for relation rows |\n| id | string | Yes | Caller-chosen logical id. Must be unique **within** a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace, see Namespace Rules below |\n| label | string | Yes | Human-readable name/caption (dimension, path, finding title, evidence anchor, etc.) |\n| relation | `\"COVERS\"` \\| `\"EVIDENCE_FOR\"` \\| `\"CONTRADICTS\"` \\| `\"RESOLVES\"` \\| `\"CONFIRMS\"` \\| `\"ESCALATES\"` \\| `\"IN_DIMENSION\"` \\| `\"IN_FILE\"` | edges only | Review relation type. Required when `type == \"edge\"` |\n| source | string | edges only | `id` of the source node inside the current namespace |\n| target | string | edges only | `id` of the target node inside the current namespace. Self-loops are rejected by the upsert handler |\n| metadata | object | No | Optional free-form metadata persisted alongside the row (e.g. `{ \"hotspot_score\": 2 }`) |\n\n#### Namespace Rules (REQ-028, REQ-029)\n\n`graphEvents` entries are scoped by the session that emits them. The coverage graph DB uses a composite primary key of `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)`, so two independent review sessions in the same spec folder MAY reuse the same logical `id` without collision, each session gets its own row.\n\nConcrete obligations for producers:\n\n1. **Session-local uniqueness**: within one session, an `id` must resolve to exactly one node (or edge) for its entire lifetime. Re-emitting the same `id` is an upsert against the existing row in that session only.\n2. **No cross-session global uniqueness requirement**: callers MUST NOT prefix ids with the session id or random salt to \"avoid collisions\". The DB layer handles namespace isolation. Salting ids only makes provenance harder to read.\n3. **Edge source/target locality**: `source` and `target` in an edge event must name nodes already present in the same namespace. Cross-session edges are not a supported shape.\n4. **Persistence gate**: the reducer refuses to roll graph events forward when a record is missing `sessionId` on the surrounding iteration record, because the DB cannot route the write.\n\nThe collision regression in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/session-isolation.vitest.ts` (\"shared-ID collisions\" block) exercises this contract directly: two sessions upsert identical node and edge ids, and both rows must survive independently.\n\n### Synthesis Event\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\", \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"totalIterations\": 6, \"verdict\": \"PASS\",\n  \"activeP0\": 0, \"activeP1\": 0, \"activeP2\": 2,\n  \"dimensionCoverage\": 1.0, \"stopReason\": \"composite_converged\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `totalIterations`, `verdict`, `activeP0`, `activeP1`, `activeP2`, `dimensionCoverage`, `stopReason`, `timestamp`\n\n### Blocked-Stop Event\n\nWhen the review legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, append a first-class `blocked_stop` event instead of silently overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n  \"gateResults\": {\n    \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n    \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n      \"pass\": false,\n      \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\"],\n      \"missing\": [\"traceability\", \"maintainability\"]\n    },\n    \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n    \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.5 },\n    \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n    \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n    \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n    \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n    \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n  },\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Cover the missing review dimensions, then resolve the active P0.\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T09:45:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-11T09-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n`gateResults` carries the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. The last two are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. See `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 for the authoritative shape.\n\n**Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `run`, `blockedBy`, `gateResults`, `recoveryStrategy`, `timestamp`, `sessionId`, `generation`\n\n### Graph Convergence Event\n\nBefore the inline 3-signal review vote is allowed to finalize STOP, the workflow must append a `graph_convergence` event for the current review lineage.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"graph_convergence\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"decision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"signals\": {\n    \"dimensionCoverage\": 1,\n    \"findingStability\": 0.88,\n    \"p0ResolutionRate\": 1,\n    \"evidenceDensity\": 1.4,\n    \"hotspotSaturation\": 0.75\n  },\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T09:44:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-11T09-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n**Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `run`, `decision`, `signals`, `blockers`, `timestamp`, `sessionId`, `generation`\n\n**Decision enum:** `CONTINUE`, `STOP_ALLOWED`, `STOP_BLOCKED`\n\n**Combined-stop rule:** Final STOP is legal only when the inline review convergence decision says STOP and the latest `graph_convergence.decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\"`. If the latest graph decision is `STOP_BLOCKED`, set `stop_blocked=true`, emit `blocked_stop`, and continue recovery instead of stopping. If the latest graph decision is `CONTINUE`, downgrade the inline STOP candidate to CONTINUE.\n\n### Normalized Pause and Recovery Events\n\nPause and recovery events MUST use the frozen shared stop-reason enum at emission time:\n\n`converged`, `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `error`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":462,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1781763337368,"end":1781763337407}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0985248d89c97d30016a338d094274819198eb3e535fcb77ab"}},"id":"prt_ed95eec95001Ldvoy5i5s3Veef","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763337411,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_i5kkWvyxpe2jD5mep6101cFG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs","offset":438,"limit":12},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n438:   return path.resolve(raw);\n439: }\n440: \n441: function resolveModelServerSocketPath(env = process.env, options = {}) {\n442:   const explicitTarget = normalizeModelServerTarget(options.listenTarget || env.HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL);\n443:   if (explicitTarget) return explicitTarget;\n444:   if (env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR?.startsWith('tcp://')) return env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR;\n445: \n446:   const rawDbDir = typeof options.dbDir === 'function' ? options.dbDir() : options.dbDir;\n447:   const socketDir = env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\n448:     ? path.resolve(env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR)\n449:     : path.resolve(rawDbDir || path.join(defaultOpencodeDir, 'skills', 'system-spec-kit', 'mcp_server', 'database'));\n\n(Showing lines 438-449 of 1474. Use offset=450 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  return path.resolve(raw);\n}\n\nfunction resolveModelServerSocketPath(env = process.env, options = {}) {\n  const explicitTarget = normalizeModelServerTarget(options.listenTarget || env.HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL);\n  if (explicitTarget) return explicitTarget;\n  if (env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR?.startsWith('tcp://')) return env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR;\n\n  const rawDbDir = typeof options.dbDir === 'function' ? options.dbDir() : options.dbDir;\n  const socketDir = env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\n    ? path.resolve(env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR)\n    : path.resolve(rawDbDir || path.join(defaultOpencodeDir, 'skills', 'system-spec-kit', 'mcp_server', 'database'));","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs","text":"  return path.resolve(raw);\n}\n\nfunction resolveModelServerSocketPath(env = process.env, options = {}) {\n  const explicitTarget = normalizeModelServerTarget(options.listenTarget || env.HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL);\n  if (explicitTarget) return explicitTarget;\n  if (env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR?.startsWith('tcp://')) return env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR;\n\n  const rawDbDir = typeof options.dbDir === 'function' ? options.dbDir() : options.dbDir;\n  const socketDir = env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\n    ? path.resolve(env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR)\n    : path.resolve(rawDbDir || path.join(defaultOpencodeDir, 'skills', 'system-spec-kit', 'mcp_server', 'database'));","lineStart":438,"lineEnd":449,"totalLines":1474,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs","time":{"start":1781763337392,"end":1781763337410}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0985248d89c97d30016a338d094294819197963242a75ef0d5"}},"id":"prt_ed95eecae001dfxwp5cOc5T3Ob","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763337413,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1xVySSFWVH5cOjngPzsZqhBN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/C-rest-of-server/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/C-rest-of-server/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Audit Scope — MCP Server Infrastructure (handlers / providers / daemon)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the system-spec-kit MCP server infrastructure OUTSIDE the search pipeline (scope A) and the store/index/lifecycle surface (scope B): the request handlers, embedding providers, daemon launcher, and server lifecycle. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n5: \n6: ## Code under review\n7: Paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` and `.opencode/bin/`:\n8: - `context-server.js`, `tool-schemas.ts`, the MCP tool dispatch + handler entry points under `handlers/` (request validation, envelopes, error taxonomy)\n9: - `lib/providers/` — embedding providers, retry-manager, provider failover/health\n10: - `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/model-server-supervision.cjs` — owner-lease, re-election, daemon supervision, socket/IPC, recycle/respawn\n11: - `lib/ipc/` / the IPC transport, secondary-client management, and the daemon-backed CLI front door (`spec-memory.cjs`)\n12: \n13: ## Review dimensions\n14: correctness, security (IPC trust boundaries, input validation, path/socket handling), concurrency (lease races, reconnect, respawn), resource lifecycle (handles, sockets, orphan processes), error taxonomy/exit codes, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize daemon lifecycle races, IPC trust, and fail-closed behavior.\n15: \n16: ## Notes\n17: This round BROADENS to the server infrastructure. Focus on handler/provider/daemon code, not the search pipeline (scope A) or store/index/lifecycle (scope B).\n\n(End of file - total 17 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Audit Scope — MCP Server Infrastructure (handlers / providers / daemon)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the system-spec-kit MCP server infrastructure OUTSIDE the search pipeline (scope A) and the store/index/lifecycle surface (scope B): the request handlers, embedding providers, daemon launcher, and server lifecycle. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nPaths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` and `.opencode/bin/`:\n- `context-server.js`, `tool-schemas.ts`, the MCP tool dispatch + handler entry points under `handlers/` (request validation, envelopes, error taxonomy)\n- `lib/providers/` — embedding providers, retry-manager, provider failover/health\n- `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/model-server-supervision.cjs` — owner-lease, re-election, daemon supervision, socket/IPC, recycle/respawn\n- `lib/ipc/` / the IPC transport, secondary-client management, and the daemon-backed CLI front door (`spec-memory.cjs`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (IPC trust boundaries, input validation, path/socket handling), concurrency (lease races, reconnect, respawn), resource lifecycle (handles, sockets, orphan processes), error taxonomy/exit codes, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize daemon lifecycle races, IPC trust, and fail-closed behavior.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS to the server infrastructure. Focus on handler/provider/daemon code, not the search pipeline (scope A) or store/index/lifecycle (scope B).","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/C-rest-of-server/spec.md","text":"# Audit Scope — MCP Server Infrastructure (handlers / providers / daemon)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the system-spec-kit MCP server infrastructure OUTSIDE the search pipeline (scope A) and the store/index/lifecycle surface (scope B): the request handlers, embedding providers, daemon launcher, and server lifecycle. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nPaths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` and `.opencode/bin/`:\n- `context-server.js`, `tool-schemas.ts`, the MCP tool dispatch + handler entry points under `handlers/` (request validation, envelopes, error taxonomy)\n- `lib/providers/` — embedding providers, retry-manager, provider failover/health\n- `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/model-server-supervision.cjs` — owner-lease, re-election, daemon supervision, socket/IPC, recycle/respawn\n- `lib/ipc/` / the IPC transport, secondary-client management, and the daemon-backed CLI front door (`spec-memory.cjs`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (IPC trust boundaries, input validation, path/socket handling), concurrency (lease races, reconnect, respawn), resource lifecycle (handles, sockets, orphan processes), error taxonomy/exit codes, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize daemon lifecycle races, IPC trust, and fail-closed behavior.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS to the server infrastructure. Focus on handler/provider/daemon code, not the search pipeline (scope A) or store/index/lifecycle (scope B).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":17,"totalLines":17,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/C-rest-of-server/spec.md","time":{"start":1781763337374,"end":1781763337412}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0985248d89c97d30016a338d09427c8191b3dafb7a1fd096db"}},"id":"prt_ed95eec9b001xVD1wfDamjV97y","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ebe32001RjEgP02gRMVj8M"}}
