{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763351667,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZSpH8rnvBTfGJoX60WuXm06O","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts","offset":213,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n213: \n214: // Only remove a stale socket at `socketPath` when it is provably ours: the parent dir resolves\n215: // inside an allowed root, the path is an actual socket, and it is owned by the current uid.\n216: // Guards against socket-hijack on shared hosts where an attacker plants a non-socket file or a\n217: // socket they own at the bind path.\n218: function canUnlinkExistingSocket(socketPath: string): boolean {\n219:   let parent: string;\n220:   try {\n221:     parent = fs.realpathSync.native(path.dirname(socketPath));\n222:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n223:     // A racing peer can remove the socket directory between the EADDRINUSE failure and this\n224:     // resolve; a vanished node is safe to reclaim, so never abort the bind on a missing path.\n225:     if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'ENOENT') {\n226:       return true;\n227:     }\n228:     throw error;\n229:   }\n230:   if (!isWithinAllowedSocketRoot(parent)) {\n231:     return false;\n232:   }\n233:   try {\n234:     const stat = fs.lstatSync(socketPath);\n235:     if (!stat.isSocket()) {\n236:       return false;\n237:     }\n238:     if (typeof process.getuid === 'function' && stat.uid !== process.getuid()) {\n239:       return false;\n240:     }\n241:     return true;\n242:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n243:     // Same race on the socket node itself: if it is already gone the prior EADDRINUSE was\n244:     // transient, so treat the path as reclaimable instead of throwing and orphaning the bind.\n245:     if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'ENOENT') {\n246:       return true;\n247:     }\n248:     throw error;\n249:   }\n250: }\n251: \n252: function getIpcBridgeStats(): IpcBridgeStats {\n253:   return {\n254:     socket_path: activeSocketPath,\n255:     secondary_clients_count: activeSockets.size,\n256:     total_secondary_messages_in: totalSecondaryMessagesIn,\n257:     total_secondary_messages_out: totalSecondaryMessagesOut,\n258:   };\n259: }\n260: \n261: async function listenOnce(server: net.Server, socketPath: string): Promise<void> {\n262:   await new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {\n263:     const onError = (error: NodeJS.ErrnoException) => {\n264:       server.off('listening', onListening);\n265:       reject(error);\n266:     };\n267:     const onListening = () => {\n268:       server.off('error', onError);\n269:       resolve();\n270:     };\n271:     server.once('error', onError);\n272:     server.once('listening', onListening);\n273:     if (socketPath.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n274:       const url = new URL(socketPath);\n275:       server.listen(Number.parseInt(url.port, 10), url.hostname);\n276:       return;\n277:     }\n278:     server.listen(socketPath);\n279:   });\n280: }\n281: \n282: // TCP fallback (used when a unix socket path exceeds the sun_path limit) cannot be reclaimed by\n283: // unlinking a node — a stale TCP port frees itself once the prior owner exits, so retry the bind a\n284: // few times before giving up. Returns true once a retry binds, false if the port stays in use.\n285: async function retryTcpListenAfterEaddrInUse(\n286:   server: net.Server,\n287:   socketPath: string,\n288:   log: (message: string) => void,\n289: ): Promise<boolean> {\n290:   for (const delayMs of TCP_EADDRINUSE_RETRY_DELAYS_MS) {\n291:     log(`[ipc-bridge] tcp socket in use at ${socketPath}; retrying listen in ${delayMs}ms`);\n292:     await sleep(delayMs);\n293:     try {\n294:       await listenOnce(server, socketPath);\n295:       return true;\n296:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n297:       const err = error as NodeJS.ErrnoException;\n298:       if (err.code !== 'EADDRINUSE') {\n299:         throw err;\n300:       }\n301:     }\n302:   }\n303:   return false;\n304: }\n305: \n306: // Tear down any server still registered in the module-global slots before a new bind reuses them.\n307: // startIpcSocketServer tracks its server/sockets in module globals, so a second start without a\n308: // dispose would orphan the prior listener (leaking the socket and its clients) and corrupt the\n309: // shared stats. Re-entrancy must close the prior server first.\n310: async function disposeActiveServer(): Promise<void> {\n311:   const priorServer = activeServer;\n312:   for (const socket of activeSockets) {\n313:     socket.destroy();\n314:   }\n315:   activeSockets.clear();\n316:   activeTransports.clear();\n317:   if (priorServer) {\n318:     await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n319:       priorServer.close(() => resolve());\n320:     });\n321:   }\n322:   activeServer = null;\n323:   activeSocketPath = null;\n324: }\n325: \n326: async function startIpcSocketServer(options: IpcSocketServerOptions): Promise<IpcSocketServerHandle> {\n327:   if (activeServer) {\n328:     await disposeActiveServer();\n329:   }\n330:   const socketPath = options.socketPath.startsWith('tcp://')\n331:     ? options.socketPath\n332:     : path.resolve(options.socketPath);\n\n(Showing lines 213-332 of 518. Use offset=333 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n// Only remove a stale socket at `socketPath` when it is provably ours: the parent dir resolves\n// inside an allowed root, the path is an actual socket, and it is owned by the current uid.\n// Guards against socket-hijack on shared hosts where an attacker plants a non-socket file or a\n// socket they own at the bind path.\nfunction canUnlinkExistingSocket(socketPath: string): boolean {\n  let parent: string;\n  try {\n    parent = fs.realpathSync.native(path.dirname(socketPath));\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    // A racing peer can remove the socket directory between the EADDRINUSE failure and this\n    // resolve; a vanished node is safe to reclaim, so never abort the bind on a missing path.\n    if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'ENOENT') {\n      return true;\n    }\n    throw error;\n  }\n  if (!isWithinAllowedSocketRoot(parent)) {\n    return false;\n  }","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts","text":"\n// Only remove a stale socket at `socketPath` when it is provably ours: the parent dir resolves\n// inside an allowed root, the path is an actual socket, and it is owned by the current uid.\n// Guards against socket-hijack on shared hosts where an attacker plants a non-socket file or a\n// socket they own at the bind path.\nfunction canUnlinkExistingSocket(socketPath: string): boolean {\n  let parent: string;\n  try {\n    parent = fs.realpathSync.native(path.dirname(socketPath));\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    // A racing peer can remove the socket directory between the EADDRINUSE failure and this\n    // resolve; a vanished node is safe to reclaim, so never abort the bind on a missing path.\n    if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'ENOENT') {\n      return true;\n    }\n    throw error;\n  }\n  if (!isWithinAllowedSocketRoot(parent)) {\n    return false;\n  }\n  try {\n    const stat = fs.lstatSync(socketPath);\n    if (!stat.isSocket()) {\n      return false;\n    }\n    if (typeof process.getuid === 'function' && stat.uid !== process.getuid()) {\n      return false;\n    }\n    return true;\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    // Same race on the socket node itself: if it is already gone the prior EADDRINUSE was\n    // transient, so treat the path as reclaimable instead of throwing and orphaning the bind.\n    if ((error as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'ENOENT') {\n      return true;\n    }\n    throw error;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction getIpcBridgeStats(): IpcBridgeStats {\n  return {\n    socket_path: activeSocketPath,\n    secondary_clients_count: activeSockets.size,\n    total_secondary_messages_in: totalSecondaryMessagesIn,\n    total_secondary_messages_out: totalSecondaryMessagesOut,\n  };\n}\n\nasync function listenOnce(server: net.Server, socketPath: string): Promise<void> {\n  await new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {\n    const onError = (error: NodeJS.ErrnoException) => {\n      server.off('listening', onListening);\n      reject(error);\n    };\n    const onListening = () => {\n      server.off('error', onError);\n      resolve();\n    };\n    server.once('error', onError);\n    server.once('listening', onListening);\n    if (socketPath.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n      const url = new URL(socketPath);\n      server.listen(Number.parseInt(url.port, 10), url.hostname);\n      return;\n    }\n    server.listen(socketPath);\n  });\n}\n\n// TCP fallback (used when a unix socket path exceeds the sun_path limit) cannot be reclaimed by\n// unlinking a node — a stale TCP port frees itself once the prior owner exits, so retry the bind a\n// few times before giving up. Returns true once a retry binds, false if the port stays in use.\nasync function retryTcpListenAfterEaddrInUse(\n  server: net.Server,\n  socketPath: string,\n  log: (message: string) => void,\n): Promise<boolean> {\n  for (const delayMs of TCP_EADDRINUSE_RETRY_DELAYS_MS) {\n    log(`[ipc-bridge] tcp socket in use at ${socketPath}; retrying listen in ${delayMs}ms`);\n    await sleep(delayMs);\n    try {\n      await listenOnce(server, socketPath);\n      return true;\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      const err = error as NodeJS.ErrnoException;\n      if (err.code !== 'EADDRINUSE') {\n        throw err;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\n// Tear down any server still registered in the module-global slots before a new bind reuses them.\n// startIpcSocketServer tracks its server/sockets in module globals, so a second start without a\n// dispose would orphan the prior listener (leaking the socket and its clients) and corrupt the\n// shared stats. Re-entrancy must close the prior server first.\nasync function disposeActiveServer(): Promise<void> {\n  const priorServer = activeServer;\n  for (const socket of activeSockets) {\n    socket.destroy();\n  }\n  activeSockets.clear();\n  activeTransports.clear();\n  if (priorServer) {\n    await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n      priorServer.close(() => resolve());\n    });\n  }\n  activeServer = null;\n  activeSocketPath = null;\n}\n\nasync function startIpcSocketServer(options: IpcSocketServerOptions): Promise<IpcSocketServerHandle> {\n  if (activeServer) {\n    await disposeActiveServer();\n  }\n  const socketPath = options.socketPath.startsWith('tcp://')\n    ? options.socketPath\n    : path.resolve(options.socketPath);","lineStart":213,"lineEnd":332,"totalLines":518,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts","time":{"start":1781763351659,"end":1781763351664}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0340b13b36e1d62e016a338d16a8b88191a2e2c65bc8b78856"}},"id":"prt_ed95f2458001dDBSsz9V9YHoGF","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ef07f001Alk44r7KCxVjBb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763351669,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f5djAXRDCwmjj1lnVEjTBJZv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // [launcher-session-proxy] Launcher-owned MCP stdin/stdout bridge over daemon IPC.\n2: 'use strict';\n3: \n4: const net = require('net');\n5: const { StringDecoder } = require('string_decoder');\n6: const {\n7:   probeDaemon,\n8:   toConnectionOptions,\n9: } = require('./launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs');\n10: \n11: const PROBE_BACKOFF_MS = [100, 250, 500, 1000, 1500];\n12: const DEFAULT_MAX_REATTACH_ATTEMPTS = 40;\n13: // Bounded so a dead/booting daemon surfaces a retryable -32001 to the client in ~tens of\n14: // seconds (~41s with the backoff ladder) instead of ~176s of silent \"connecting…\". A healthy\n15: // daemon answers the deep probe within the first few attempts; the only thing this shortens is\n16: // the pathological wait when the backend cannot come up. Tunable via SPECKIT_PROXY_COLD_START_ATTEMPTS.\n17: const DEFAULT_MAX_COLD_START_ATTEMPTS = 30;\n18: const INTERNAL_HANDSHAKE_TIMEOUT_MS = 7000;\n19: const DEFAULT_KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL_MS = 10_000;\n20: const DEFAULT_KEEPALIVE_TIMEOUT_MS = 5_000;\n21: const DEFAULT_MAX_QUEUED_CLIENT_FRAMES = 1000;\n22: const PROXY_PRIVATE_ID_PREFIX = '__launcher_session_proxy_keepalive__';\n23: const RETRYABLE_RECYCLE_ERROR = Object.freeze({\n24:   code: -32001,\n25:   message: 'backend recycled; retry',\n26:   data: { retryable: true },\n27: });\n28: const PROTOCOL_MISMATCH_ERROR = Object.freeze({\n29:   code: -32002,\n30:   message: 'backend protocol version changed; client reconnect required',\n31:   data: { retryable: false },\n32: });\n33: const REPLAYABLE_TOOL_NAMES = new Set([\n34:   'memory_search',\n35:   'memory_context',\n36:   'memory_match_triggers',\n37:   'memory_quick_search',\n38:   'memory_save',\n39:   'session_bootstrap',\n40:   'session_health',\n41:   'session_resume',\n42:   'session_status',\n43:   'memory_stats',\n44:   'memory_status',\n45:   'checkpoint_list',\n46:   'embedder_health',\n47: ]);\n48: const UNSAFE_TOOL_NAMES = new Set([\n49:   'memory_delete',\n50:   'memory_bulk_delete',\n51:   'memory_update',\n52:   'checkpoint_restore',\n53:   'checkpoint_delete',\n54:   'embedder_set',\n55:   'memory_retention_sweep',\n56:   'memory_ingest_start',\n57:   'memory_ingest_cancel',\n58: ]);\n59: const REPLAYABLE_PROTOCOL_METHODS = new Set([\n60:   'initialize',\n61:   'ping',\n62: ]);\n63: \n64: const sleep = (ms) => new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n65: \n66: function defaultConnect(connectionOptions) {\n67:   return net.createConnection(connectionOptions);\n68: }\n69: \n70: function defaultLog(message) {\n71:   process.stderr.write(`[launcher-session-proxy] ${message}\\n`);\n72: }\n73: \n74: function createFrameSplitter(onFrame) {\n75:   let buffer = '';\n76:   // A multibyte UTF-8 char (CJK/emoji) can straddle a socket-chunk boundary; the\n77:   // StringDecoder holds the incomplete tail until the next chunk completes it, instead\n78:   // of emitting U+FFFD replacement chars on the partial sequence.\n79:   const decoder = new StringDecoder('utf8');\n80:   return {\n81:     push(chunk) {\n82:       buffer += Buffer.isBuffer(chunk) ? decoder.write(chunk) : String(chunk ?? '');\n83:       let newlineIndex = buffer.indexOf('\\n');\n84:       while (newlineIndex !== -1) {\n85:         const frame = buffer.slice(0, newlineIndex);\n86:         buffer = buffer.slice(newlineIndex + 1);\n87:         newlineIndex = buffer.indexOf('\\n');\n88:         if (frame.trim().length === 0) continue;\n89:         onFrame(frame);\n90:       }\n\n(Showing lines 1-90 of 853. Use offset=91 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// [launcher-session-proxy] Launcher-owned MCP stdin/stdout bridge over daemon IPC.\n'use strict';\n\nconst net = require('net');\nconst { StringDecoder } = require('string_decoder');\nconst {\n  probeDaemon,\n  toConnectionOptions,\n} = require('./launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs');\n\nconst PROBE_BACKOFF_MS = [100, 250, 500, 1000, 1500];\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_REATTACH_ATTEMPTS = 40;\n// Bounded so a dead/booting daemon surfaces a retryable -32001 to the client in ~tens of\n// seconds (~41s with the backoff ladder) instead of ~176s of silent \"connecting…\". A healthy\n// daemon answers the deep probe within the first few attempts; the only thing this shortens is\n// the pathological wait when the backend cannot come up. Tunable via SPECKIT_PROXY_COLD_START_ATTEMPTS.\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_COLD_START_ATTEMPTS = 30;\nconst INTERNAL_HANDSHAKE_TIMEOUT_MS = 7000;\nconst DEFAULT_KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL_MS = 10_000;\nconst DEFAULT_KEEPALIVE_TIMEOUT_MS = 5_000;","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs","text":"// [launcher-session-proxy] Launcher-owned MCP stdin/stdout bridge over daemon IPC.\n'use strict';\n\nconst net = require('net');\nconst { StringDecoder } = require('string_decoder');\nconst {\n  probeDaemon,\n  toConnectionOptions,\n} = require('./launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs');\n\nconst PROBE_BACKOFF_MS = [100, 250, 500, 1000, 1500];\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_REATTACH_ATTEMPTS = 40;\n// Bounded so a dead/booting daemon surfaces a retryable -32001 to the client in ~tens of\n// seconds (~41s with the backoff ladder) instead of ~176s of silent \"connecting…\". A healthy\n// daemon answers the deep probe within the first few attempts; the only thing this shortens is\n// the pathological wait when the backend cannot come up. Tunable via SPECKIT_PROXY_COLD_START_ATTEMPTS.\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_COLD_START_ATTEMPTS = 30;\nconst INTERNAL_HANDSHAKE_TIMEOUT_MS = 7000;\nconst DEFAULT_KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL_MS = 10_000;\nconst DEFAULT_KEEPALIVE_TIMEOUT_MS = 5_000;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_QUEUED_CLIENT_FRAMES = 1000;\nconst PROXY_PRIVATE_ID_PREFIX = '__launcher_session_proxy_keepalive__';\nconst RETRYABLE_RECYCLE_ERROR = Object.freeze({\n  code: -32001,\n  message: 'backend recycled; retry',\n  data: { retryable: true },\n});\nconst PROTOCOL_MISMATCH_ERROR = Object.freeze({\n  code: -32002,\n  message: 'backend protocol version changed; client reconnect required',\n  data: { retryable: false },\n});\nconst REPLAYABLE_TOOL_NAMES = new Set([\n  'memory_search',\n  'memory_context',\n  'memory_match_triggers',\n  'memory_quick_search',\n  'memory_save',\n  'session_bootstrap',\n  'session_health',\n  'session_resume',\n  'session_status',\n  'memory_stats',\n  'memory_status',\n  'checkpoint_list',\n  'embedder_health',\n]);\nconst UNSAFE_TOOL_NAMES = new Set([\n  'memory_delete',\n  'memory_bulk_delete',\n  'memory_update',\n  'checkpoint_restore',\n  'checkpoint_delete',\n  'embedder_set',\n  'memory_retention_sweep',\n  'memory_ingest_start',\n  'memory_ingest_cancel',\n]);\nconst REPLAYABLE_PROTOCOL_METHODS = new Set([\n  'initialize',\n  'ping',\n]);\n\nconst sleep = (ms) => new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n\nfunction defaultConnect(connectionOptions) {\n  return net.createConnection(connectionOptions);\n}\n\nfunction defaultLog(message) {\n  process.stderr.write(`[launcher-session-proxy] ${message}\\n`);\n}\n\nfunction createFrameSplitter(onFrame) {\n  let buffer = '';\n  // A multibyte UTF-8 char (CJK/emoji) can straddle a socket-chunk boundary; the\n  // StringDecoder holds the incomplete tail until the next chunk completes it, instead\n  // of emitting U+FFFD replacement chars on the partial sequence.\n  const decoder = new StringDecoder('utf8');\n  return {\n    push(chunk) {\n      buffer += Buffer.isBuffer(chunk) ? decoder.write(chunk) : String(chunk ?? '');\n      let newlineIndex = buffer.indexOf('\\n');\n      while (newlineIndex !== -1) {\n        const frame = buffer.slice(0, newlineIndex);\n        buffer = buffer.slice(newlineIndex + 1);\n        newlineIndex = buffer.indexOf('\\n');\n        if (frame.trim().length === 0) continue;\n        onFrame(frame);\n      }","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":90,"totalLines":853,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs","time":{"start":1781763351666,"end":1781763351668}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0340b13b36e1d62e016a338d16a8cc8191816bc606bce7aebd"}},"id":"prt_ed95f246e001wTHCzIHCIoRE6d","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ef07f001Alk44r7KCxVjBb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763351686,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0xO8J1BBAgrFEUe9pdzXwjNk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs","offset":130,"limit":35},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n130:   return function classify(frame) {\n131:     const parsed = typeof frame === 'string' ? parseFrame(frame) : frame;\n132:     if (!parsed || typeof parsed.method !== 'string') return false;\n133:     if (parsed.method !== 'tools/call') {\n134:       return REPLAYABLE_PROTOCOL_METHODS.has(parsed.method) || parsed.method.startsWith('notifications/');\n135:     }\n136:     const toolName = parsed.params && typeof parsed.params === 'object'\n137:       ? parsed.params.name\n138:       : undefined;\n139:     if (typeof toolName !== 'string') return false;\n140:     if (unsafe.has(toolName)) return false;\n141:     if (replayable.has(toolName)) return true;\n142:     return false;\n143:   };\n144: }\n145: \n146: // Default classifier uses the mk-spec-memory tool sets. memory_save is replayable on a\n147: // commit-then-die backend because its primary row is protected by content-hash dedup AND the v28\n148: // active-row partial unique index (idx_memory_logical_key_active_unique): an identical-content replay\n149: // collapses to the same logical key and writes no new primary row. The KNOWN GAP is the secondary\n150: // index — a commit-then-die that finished the primary insert but not the secondary-index write can,\n151: // on replay, append duplicate secondary-index rows because that path is not yet keyed by an\n152: // idempotency token. Closing it requires a request-id/dedup key threaded into the save handler, which\n153: // lives behind the daemon IPC and is out of scope for this proxy-layer frame classifier.\n154: const classifyFrame = createClassifyFrame();\n155: \n156: function createPendingRequestsTracker(classify = classifyFrame) {\n157:   const pendingRequests = new Map();\n158:   let cachedInitialize = null;\n159:   let cachedInitializeId = null;\n160:   let negotiatedProtocolVersion = null;\n161:   let protocolVersionObserved = false;\n162: \n163:   function handleClientFrame(frame) {\n164:     const parsed = parseFrame(frame);\n\n(Showing lines 130-164 of 853. Use offset=165 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  return function classify(frame) {\n    const parsed = typeof frame === 'string' ? parseFrame(frame) : frame;\n    if (!parsed || typeof parsed.method !== 'string') return false;\n    if (parsed.method !== 'tools/call') {\n      return REPLAYABLE_PROTOCOL_METHODS.has(parsed.method) || parsed.method.startsWith('notifications/');\n    }\n    const toolName = parsed.params && typeof parsed.params === 'object'\n      ? parsed.params.name\n      : undefined;\n    if (typeof toolName !== 'string') return false;\n    if (unsafe.has(toolName)) return false;\n    if (replayable.has(toolName)) return true;\n    return false;\n  };\n}\n\n// Default classifier uses the mk-spec-memory tool sets. memory_save is replayable on a\n// commit-then-die backend because its primary row is protected by content-hash dedup AND the v28\n// active-row partial unique index (idx_memory_logical_key_active_unique): an identical-content replay\n// collapses to the same logical key and writes no new primary row. The KNOWN GAP is the secondary","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs","text":"  return function classify(frame) {\n    const parsed = typeof frame === 'string' ? parseFrame(frame) : frame;\n    if (!parsed || typeof parsed.method !== 'string') return false;\n    if (parsed.method !== 'tools/call') {\n      return REPLAYABLE_PROTOCOL_METHODS.has(parsed.method) || parsed.method.startsWith('notifications/');\n    }\n    const toolName = parsed.params && typeof parsed.params === 'object'\n      ? parsed.params.name\n      : undefined;\n    if (typeof toolName !== 'string') return false;\n    if (unsafe.has(toolName)) return false;\n    if (replayable.has(toolName)) return true;\n    return false;\n  };\n}\n\n// Default classifier uses the mk-spec-memory tool sets. memory_save is replayable on a\n// commit-then-die backend because its primary row is protected by content-hash dedup AND the v28\n// active-row partial unique index (idx_memory_logical_key_active_unique): an identical-content replay\n// collapses to the same logical key and writes no new primary row. The KNOWN GAP is the secondary\n// index — a commit-then-die that finished the primary insert but not the secondary-index write can,\n// on replay, append duplicate secondary-index rows because that path is not yet keyed by an\n// idempotency token. Closing it requires a request-id/dedup key threaded into the save handler, which\n// lives behind the daemon IPC and is out of scope for this proxy-layer frame classifier.\nconst classifyFrame = createClassifyFrame();\n\nfunction createPendingRequestsTracker(classify = classifyFrame) {\n  const pendingRequests = new Map();\n  let cachedInitialize = null;\n  let cachedInitializeId = null;\n  let negotiatedProtocolVersion = null;\n  let protocolVersionObserved = false;\n\n  function handleClientFrame(frame) {\n    const parsed = parseFrame(frame);","lineStart":130,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":853,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs","time":{"start":1781763351682,"end":1781763351685}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0340b13b36e1d62e016a338d16a8d88191aa9ef45ecc0e186e"}},"id":"prt_ed95f2477001bBY6JnEgUzYMNW","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ef07f001Alk44r7KCxVjBb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763351699,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tcgwMmCs18qDmXGcbiBcceF4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts","offset":258,"limit":37},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n258:   it('classifies replayable and unsafe calls with default-deny for unknown tools', () => {\n259:     const replayableTools = [\n260:       'memory_search',\n261:       'memory_context',\n262:       'memory_match_triggers',\n263:       'memory_quick_search',\n264:       'memory_save',\n265:       'session_bootstrap',\n266:       'session_health',\n267:       'session_resume',\n268:       'session_status',\n269:       'memory_stats',\n270:       'checkpoint_list',\n271:       'embedder_health',\n272:       'memory_status',\n273:     ];\n274:     const unsafeTools = [\n275:       'memory_delete',\n276:       'memory_bulk_delete',\n277:       'memory_update',\n278:       'checkpoint_restore',\n279:       'checkpoint_delete',\n280:       'embedder_set',\n281:       'memory_retention_sweep',\n282:       'memory_ingest_start',\n283:       'memory_ingest_cancel',\n284:     ];\n285: \n286:     for (const name of replayableTools) {\n287:       expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall(name, name))).toBe(true);\n288:     }\n289:     for (const name of unsafeTools) {\n290:       expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall(name, name))).toBe(false);\n291:     }\n292: \n293:     expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall('unknown', 'unlisted_mutator'))).toBe(false);\n294:     expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall('unknown-status', 'something_status'))).toBe(false);\n\n(Showing lines 258-294 of 706. Use offset=295 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  it('classifies replayable and unsafe calls with default-deny for unknown tools', () => {\n    const replayableTools = [\n      'memory_search',\n      'memory_context',\n      'memory_match_triggers',\n      'memory_quick_search',\n      'memory_save',\n      'session_bootstrap',\n      'session_health',\n      'session_resume',\n      'session_status',\n      'memory_stats',\n      'checkpoint_list',\n      'embedder_health',\n      'memory_status',\n    ];\n    const unsafeTools = [\n      'memory_delete',\n      'memory_bulk_delete',\n      'memory_update',","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts","text":"  it('classifies replayable and unsafe calls with default-deny for unknown tools', () => {\n    const replayableTools = [\n      'memory_search',\n      'memory_context',\n      'memory_match_triggers',\n      'memory_quick_search',\n      'memory_save',\n      'session_bootstrap',\n      'session_health',\n      'session_resume',\n      'session_status',\n      'memory_stats',\n      'checkpoint_list',\n      'embedder_health',\n      'memory_status',\n    ];\n    const unsafeTools = [\n      'memory_delete',\n      'memory_bulk_delete',\n      'memory_update',\n      'checkpoint_restore',\n      'checkpoint_delete',\n      'embedder_set',\n      'memory_retention_sweep',\n      'memory_ingest_start',\n      'memory_ingest_cancel',\n    ];\n\n    for (const name of replayableTools) {\n      expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall(name, name))).toBe(true);\n    }\n    for (const name of unsafeTools) {\n      expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall(name, name))).toBe(false);\n    }\n\n    expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall('unknown', 'unlisted_mutator'))).toBe(false);\n    expect(__testing.classifyFrame(toolCall('unknown-status', 'something_status'))).toBe(false);","lineStart":258,"lineEnd":294,"totalLines":706,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts","time":{"start":1781763351691,"end":1781763351698}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0340b13b36e1d62e016a338d16a8e881919848886476e9f56b"}},"id":"prt_ed95f2483001Y2OO9jvwZIDs9n","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ef07f001Alk44r7KCxVjBb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763351714,"sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e1dVYAtU45gQ0x0HbS4q60Sm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md","offset":264,"limit":5},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n264: | Post-crash whole-DB integrity gate | When the `.unclean-shutdown` marker is present at open, the store also runs `PRAGMA quick_check` against the main database. On failure it writes the checkpoint `.needs-rebuild` sentinel and refuses to serve rather than expose a corrupted index; clean shutdowns skip the probe entirely. |\n265: | RSS-ceiling watchdog | Opt-in (`SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_RSS_SELF_EXIT=1`): on a sustained RSS breach the launcher SIGTERMs the child and exits cleanly so the host can relaunch. Unexpected child exits route through a crash-loop-guarded supervisor with exponential backoff. |\n266: | MCP front-proxy recycle | The launcher fronts the backend with a session proxy (`bridgeStdioThroughSessionProxy` in `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`; `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`). It keeps one stable client session while the backend recycles in place (RSS restart, rebuild) and transparently replays read and idempotent-write tools across the recycle (`memory_save` is replayable because it relies on primary-row dedup). Known gap: a replay after the primary insert but before secondary-index writes can append duplicate secondary-index rows because that path is not yet keyed by an idempotency token. `SPECKIT_BACKEND_ONLY=1` makes a process run purely as that recyclable backend. |\n267: | Recycle/reconnect error codes | `-32001` `RETRYABLE_RECYCLE_ERROR` (`backend recycled; retry`, `data.retryable: true`) is the **live** recycle signal the proxy emits while the backend restarts — clients retry; it is **not removed** (only the index vector-drain outage path stopped surfacing its own `-32001`). `-32002` `PROTOCOL_MISMATCH_ERROR` (`data.retryable: false`) is the fail-closed protocol break that moves the proxy to terminal CLOSED and forces a fresh client reconnect. |\n268: | Rebuild + recycle helper | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/deploy-mcp.sh` is the canonical helper to rebuild every MCP server `dist/` (mk-spec-memory + `@spec-kit/shared`, code-graph, advisor) after a source change. `dist/` is gitignored, so rebuild after pulling source changes. Passing `--recycle` drives the *MCP front-proxy recycle* row above for mk-spec-memory (transparent); code-graph and advisor are not SIGTERM-recycled (their launchers exit, so fresh dist loads on next start). Launcher `.cjs` changes need a FRESH session and cannot be picked up by a recycle. |\n\n(Showing lines 264-268 of 311. Use offset=269 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| Post-crash whole-DB integrity gate | When the `.unclean-shutdown` marker is present at open, the store also runs `PRAGMA quick_check` against the main database. On failure it writes the checkpoint `.needs-rebuild` sentinel and refuses to serve rather than expose a corrupted index; clean shutdowns skip the probe entirely. |\n| RSS-ceiling watchdog | Opt-in (`SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_RSS_SELF_EXIT=1`): on a sustained RSS breach the launcher SIGTERMs the child and exits cleanly so the host can relaunch. Unexpected child exits route through a crash-loop-guarded supervisor with exponential backoff. |\n| MCP front-proxy recycle | The launcher fronts the backend with a session proxy (`bridgeStdioThroughSessionProxy` in `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`; `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`). It keeps one stable client session while the backend recycles in place (RSS restart, rebuild) and transparently replays read and idempotent-write tools across the recycle (`memory_save` is replayable because it relies on primary-row dedup). Known gap: a replay after the primary insert but before secondary-index writes can append duplicate secondary-index rows because that path is not yet keyed by an idempotency token. `SPECKIT_BACKEND_ONLY=1` makes a process run purely as that recyclable backend. |\n| Recycle/reconnect error codes | `-32001` `RETRYABLE_RECYCLE_ERROR` (`backend recycled; retry`, `data.retryable: true`) is the **live** recycle signal the proxy emits while the backend restarts — clients retry; it is **not removed** (only the index vector-drain outage path stopped surfacing its own `-32001`). `-32002` `PROTOCOL_MISMATCH_ERROR` (`data.retryable: false`) is the fail-closed protocol break that moves the proxy to terminal CLOSED and forces a fresh client reconnect. |\n| Rebuild + recycle helper | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/deploy-mcp.sh` is the canonical helper to rebuild every MCP server `dist/` (mk-spec-memory + `@spec-kit/shared`, code-graph, advisor) after a source change. `dist/` is gitignored, so rebuild after pulling source changes. Passing `--recycle` drives the *MCP front-proxy recycle* row above for mk-spec-memory (transparent); code-graph and advisor are not SIGTERM-recycled (their launchers exit, so fresh dist loads on next start). Launcher `.cjs` changes need a FRESH session and cannot be picked up by a recycle. |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md","text":"| Post-crash whole-DB integrity gate | When the `.unclean-shutdown` marker is present at open, the store also runs `PRAGMA quick_check` against the main database. On failure it writes the checkpoint `.needs-rebuild` sentinel and refuses to serve rather than expose a corrupted index; clean shutdowns skip the probe entirely. |\n| RSS-ceiling watchdog | Opt-in (`SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_RSS_SELF_EXIT=1`): on a sustained RSS breach the launcher SIGTERMs the child and exits cleanly so the host can relaunch. Unexpected child exits route through a crash-loop-guarded supervisor with exponential backoff. |\n| MCP front-proxy recycle | The launcher fronts the backend with a session proxy (`bridgeStdioThroughSessionProxy` in `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`; `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`). It keeps one stable client session while the backend recycles in place (RSS restart, rebuild) and transparently replays read and idempotent-write tools across the recycle (`memory_save` is replayable because it relies on primary-row dedup). Known gap: a replay after the primary insert but before secondary-index writes can append duplicate secondary-index rows because that path is not yet keyed by an idempotency token. `SPECKIT_BACKEND_ONLY=1` makes a process run purely as that recyclable backend. |\n| Recycle/reconnect error codes | `-32001` `RETRYABLE_RECYCLE_ERROR` (`backend recycled; retry`, `data.retryable: true`) is the **live** recycle signal the proxy emits while the backend restarts — clients retry; it is **not removed** (only the index vector-drain outage path stopped surfacing its own `-32001`). `-32002` `PROTOCOL_MISMATCH_ERROR` (`data.retryable: false`) is the fail-closed protocol break that moves the proxy to terminal CLOSED and forces a fresh client reconnect. |\n| Rebuild + recycle helper | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/deploy-mcp.sh` is the canonical helper to rebuild every MCP server `dist/` (mk-spec-memory + `@spec-kit/shared`, code-graph, advisor) after a source change. `dist/` is gitignored, so rebuild after pulling source changes. Passing `--recycle` drives the *MCP front-proxy recycle* row above for mk-spec-memory (transparent); code-graph and advisor are not SIGTERM-recycled (their launchers exit, so fresh dist loads on next start). Launcher `.cjs` changes need a FRESH session and cannot be picked up by a recycle. |","lineStart":264,"lineEnd":268,"totalLines":311,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md","time":{"start":1781763351706,"end":1781763351713}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0340b13b36e1d62e016a338d16a8f08191a805cead92cf5a99"}},"id":"prt_ed95f2491001GVjE2pA8LPBFyl","sessionID":"ses_126a7351cffe2yu58i7OdmNdV8","messageID":"msg_ed95ef07f001Alk44r7KCxVjBb"}}
