ity\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"],\"resource_map_present\":false,\"sessionId\":\"gpt55r2-c-6\",\"parentSessionId\":\"review-r2\",\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":1,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.1,\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-18T06:20:00Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-c-6\",\"status\":\"initialized\",\"lineageBinding\":{\"resolveArtifactRootUsed\":false}}\n-{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"C-rest-of-server daemon IPC, reconnect/replay, path/socket handling, and fail-closed behavior\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/C-rest-of-server/spec.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/context-server.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts\",\".opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs\",\".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs\",\".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs\",\".opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/stress_test/durability/daemon-recycle-transparency-stress.vitest.ts\"],\"sessionId\":\"gpt55r2-c-6\",\"parentSessionId\":\"review-r2\",\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"findingsCount\":2,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[{\"id\":\"P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Spec-memory TCP IPC endpoint is documented and launcher-supported but the server resolver rewrites it into a filesystem path\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts:201\",\"evidence\":\"ENV_REFERENCE documents SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR as accepting tcp://host:port; the CLI and launcher bridge preserve tcp:// endpoints, but resolveIpcSocketPath path-resolves the env value and appends daemon-ipc.sock before startIpcSocketServer can take its TCP branch.\",\"recommendation\":\"Teach resolveIpcSocketPath to return tcp:// targets unchanged, or remove TCP support from docs/launcher paths; add an integration test that starts the spec-memory backend with SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR=tcp://127.0.0.1:<port> and proves launcher/client attach succeeds.\",\"disposition\":\"active\",\"findingClass\":\"ipc-contract-drift\",\"finding_class\":\"ipc-contract-drift\",\"scopeProof\":\"Scope C calls out daemon lifecycle, IPC trust, socket handling, and fail-closed behavior; cited files are the spec-memory MCP server IPC path and daemon CLI bridge.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\",\"spec-memory daemon IPC\",\"launcher secondary-client bridge\",\"macOS sun_path workaround\"],\"content_hash\":\"sha256:gpt55r2c6-p1-001-ipc-tcp-contract\"},{\"id\":\"P1-002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"memory_save is replayed across backend recycle while the secondary-index write path is explicitly non-idempotent\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs:33\",\"evidence\":\"REPLAYABLE_TOOL_NAMES includes memory_save; the adjacent proxy comment and README both document that a replay after primary insert but before secondary-index writes can append duplicate secondary-index rows because no idempotency token keys that path. Tests assert memory_save remains replayable.\",\"recommendation\":\"Either classify memory_save as unsafe/non-replayable until the save handler has a request idempotency key across primary and secondary index writes, or add a secondary-index uniqueness/dedup transaction that makes replay safe and prove it with a commit-then-die recycle regression test.\",\"disposition\":\"active\",\"findingClass\":\"replay-idempotency-gap\",\"finding_class\":\"replay-idempotency-gap\",\"scopeProof\":\"Scope C includes reconnect/respawn, daemon lifecycle races, and fail-closed behavior; cited files are the launcher session proxy, durability stress tests, and server infrastructure README.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"backend recycle\",\"memory_save\",\"secondary indexes\",\"launcher session proxy\"],\"content_hash\":\"sha256:gpt55r2c6-p1-002-memory-save-replay\"}],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.42,\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"spec_code\":{\"status\":\"covered\",\"evidence\":[\"Scope C spec lines 7-14 mapped to daemon IPC and reconnect/replay files.\"],\"gaps\":[]},\"checklist_evidence\":{\"status\":\"not_applicable\",\"evidence\":[\"Review scope packet has no checklist; iteration evidence is file:line based.\"],\"gaps\":[]}},\"coverage\":{\"dimensionsCovered\":[\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"],\"dimensionCoverage\":1,\"requiredTraceabilityProtocolsCovered\":true,\"maxIterationsReached\":true},\"noveltyJustification\":\"First lineage pass for C-rest-of-server identified two active P1 infrastructure risks not requiring speculative behavior beyond documented code paths and tests.\",\"ruledOut\":[\"No P0 assigned to TCP IPC because tcp:// is opt-in configuration and current behavior is an availability/contract failure, not a default remote-exposure proof.\",\"No P0 assigned to memory_save replay because duplicate secondary rows require a backend recycle in a commit-then-die window; impact is data integrity and retrieval correctness risk, not deterministic loss on every save.\"],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.42,\"madScore\":0,\"dimensionCoverage\":1,\"compositeStop\":0.45,\"stopLegal\":true,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\"},\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-18T06:25:00Z\",\"durationMs\":150000}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"C-rest-of-server daemon IPC, reconnect/replay, path/socket handling, and fail-closed behavior\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/C-rest-of-server/spec.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/context-server.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts\",\".opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs\",\".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs\",\".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs\",\".opencode/bin/lib/model-server-supervision.cjs\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/launcher-session-proxy.vitest.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/stress_test/durability/daemon-recycle-transparency-stress.vitest.ts\"],\"sessionId\":\"gpt55r2-c-6\",\"parentSessionId\":\"review-r2\",\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"findingsCount\":2,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[{\"id\":\"P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Spec-memory TCP IPC endpoint is documented and launcher-supported but the server resolver rewrites it into a filesystem path\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/ipc/socket-server.ts:201\",\"evidence\":\"ENV_REFERENCE documents SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR as accepting tcp://host:port; the CLI and launcher bridge preserve tcp:// endpoints, but resolveIpcSocketPath path-resolves the env value and appends daemon-ipc.sock before startIpcSocketServer can take its TCP branch.\",\"recommendation\":\"Teach resolveIpcSocketPath to return tcp:// targets unchanged, or remove TCP support from docs/launcher paths; add an integration test that starts the spec-memory backend with SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR=tcp://127.0.0.1:<port> and proves launcher/client attach succeeds.\",\"disposition\":\"active\",\"findingClass\":\"ipc-contract-drift\",\"finding_class\":\"ipc-contract-drift\",\"scopeProof\":\"Scope C calls out daemon lifecycle, IPC trust, socket handling, and fail-closed behavior; cited files are the spec-memory MCP server IPC path and daemon CLI bridge.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\",\"spec-memory daemon IPC\",\"launcher secondary-client bridge\",\"macOS sun_path workaround\"],\"content_hash\":\"sha256:a639be3c4593bc14dde1fa381992e86a02d6ddc08ad1cb9c671fd132d37cb5b9\"},{\"id\":\"P1-002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"memory_save is replayed across backend recycle while the secondary-index write path is explicitly non-idempotent\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs:33\",\"evidence\":\"REPLAYABLE_TOOL_NAMES includes memory_save; the adjacent proxy comment and README both document that a replay after primary insert but before secondary-index writes can append duplicate secondary-index rows because no idempotency token keys that path. Tests assert memory_save remains replayable.\",\"recommendation\":\"Either classify memory_save as unsafe/non-replayable until the save handler has a request idempotency key across primary and secondary index writes, or add a secondary-index uniqueness/dedup transaction that makes replay safe and prove it with a commit-then-die recycle regression test.\",\"disposition\":\"active\",\"findingClass\":\"replay-idempotency-gap\",\"finding_class\":\"replay-idempotency-gap\",\"scopeProof\":\"Scope C includes reconnect/respawn, daemon lifecycle races, and fail-closed behavior; cited files are the launcher session proxy, durability stress tests, and server infrastructure README.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"backend recycle\",\"memory_save\",\"secondary indexes\",\"launcher session proxy\"],\"content_hash\":\"sha256:cffc39a35b3b77c4a08642ddcdf5179a008fbb1f7942bbc337f3165e5a392c3b\"}],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.42,\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"spec_code\":{\"status\":\"covered\",\"evidence\":[\"Scope C spec lines 7-14 mapped to daemon IPC and reconnect/replay files.\"],\"gaps\":[]},\"checklist_evidence\":{\"status\":\"not_applicable\",\"evidence\":[\"Review scope packet has no checklist; iteration evidence is file:line based.\"],\"gaps\":[]}},\"coverage\":{\"dimensionsCovered\":[\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"],\"dimensionCoverage\":1,\"requiredTraceabilityProtocolsCovered\":true,\"maxIterationsReached\":true},\"noveltyJustification\":\"First lineage pass for C-rest-of-server identified two active P1 infrastructure risks not requiring speculative behavior beyond documented code paths and tests.\",\"ruledOut\":[\"No P0 assigned to TCP IPC because tcp:// is opt-in configuration and current behavior is an availability/contract failure, not a default remote-exposure proof.\",\"No P0 assigned to memory_save replay because duplicate secondary rows require a backend recycle in a commit-then-die window; impact is data integrity and retrieval correctness risk, not deterministic loss on every save.\"],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.42,\"madScore\":0,\"dimensionCoverage\":1,\"compositeStop\":0.45,\"stopLegal\":true,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\"},\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-18T06:25:00Z\",\"durationMs\":150000}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":1,\"verdict\":\"CONDITIONAL\",\"activeP0\":0,\"activeP1\":2,\"activeP2\":0,\"dimensionCoverage\":1,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterati